34 /// Return the register values for the operands of a Phi instruction. ----
35 /// This function assume the instruction is a Phi. ----
36 static void getPhiRegs(MachineInstr &Phi, MachineBasicBlock *Loop, 0
37 unsigned &InitVal, unsigned &LoopVal) { ----
38 assert(Phi.isPHI() && "Expecting a Phi."); 0
39 ----
40 InitVal = 0; 0
41 LoopVal = 0; 0
42 for (unsigned i = 1, e = Phi.getNumOperands(); i != e; i += 2) 0
43 if (Phi.getOperand(i + 1).getMBB() != Loop) 0
44 InitVal = Phi.getOperand(i).getReg(); 0
45 else ----
46 LoopVal = Phi.getOperand(i).getReg(); 0
47 ----
48 assert(InitVal != 0 && LoopVal != 0 && "Unexpected Phi structure."); 0
49 } 0
50 ----
51 /// Return the Phi register value that comes from the incoming block. ----
52 static unsigned getInitPhiReg(MachineInstr &Phi, MachineBasicBlock *LoopBB) { 0
53 for (unsigned i = 1, e = Phi.getNumOperands(); i != e; i += 2) 0
54 if (Phi.getOperand(i + 1).getMBB() != LoopBB) 0
55 return Phi.getOperand(i).getReg(); 0
56 return 0; 0
57 } ----
58 ----
59 /// Return the Phi register value that comes the loop block. ----
60 static unsigned getLoopPhiReg(MachineInstr &Phi, MachineBasicBlock *LoopBB) { 0
61 for (unsigned i = 1, e = Phi.getNumOperands(); i != e; i += 2) 0
62 if (Phi.getOperand(i + 1).getMBB() == LoopBB) 0
63 return Phi.getOperand(i).getReg(); 0
64 return 0; 0
65 } ----

67 void ModuloScheduleExpander::expand() { 0
68 BB = Schedule.getLoop()->getTopBlock(); 0
69 Preheader = *BB->pred_begin(); 0
70 if (Preheader == BB) 0
71 Preheader = *std::next(BB->pred_begin()); 0
72 ----
73 // Iterate over the definitions in each instruction, and compute the ----
74 // stage difference for each use. Keep the maximum value. ----
75 for (MachineInstr *MI : Schedule.getInstructions()) { 0
76 int DefStage = Schedule.getStage(MI); 0
77 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI->all_defs()) { 0
78 Register Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
79 unsigned MaxDiff = 0; 0
80 bool PhiIsSwapped = false; 0
81 for (MachineOperand &UseOp : MRI.use_operands(Reg)) { 0
82 MachineInstr *UseMI = UseOp.getParent(); 0
83 int UseStage = Schedule.getStage(UseMI); 0
84 unsigned Diff = 0; 0
85 if (UseStage != -1 && UseStage >= DefStage) 0
86 Diff = UseStage - DefStage; 0
87 if (MI->isPHI()) { 0
88 if (isLoopCarried(*MI)) 0
89 ++Diff; 0
90 else ----
91 PhiIsSwapped = true; 0
92 } ----
93 MaxDiff = std::max(Diff, MaxDiff); 0
94 } ----
95 RegToStageDiff[Reg] = std::make_pair(MaxDiff, PhiIsSwapped); 0
96 } ----
97 } ----
98 ----
99 generatePipelinedLoop(); 0
100 } 0

102 void ModuloScheduleExpander::generatePipelinedLoop() { 0
103 LoopInfo = TII->analyzeLoopForPipelining(BB); 0
104 assert(LoopInfo && "Must be able to analyze loop!"); 0
105 ----
106 // Create a new basic block for the kernel and add it to the CFG. ----
107 MachineBasicBlock *KernelBB = MF.CreateMachineBasicBlock(BB->getBasicBlock()); 0
108 ----
109 unsigned MaxStageCount = Schedule.getNumStages() - 1; 0
110 ----
111 // Remember the registers that are used in different stages. The index is ----
112 // the iteration, or stage, that the instruction is scheduled in. This is ----
113 // a map between register names in the original block and the names created ----
114 // in each stage of the pipelined loop. ----
115 ValueMapTy *VRMap = new ValueMapTy[(MaxStageCount + 1) * 2]; 0
116 ----
117 // The renaming destination by Phis for the registers across stages. ----
118 // This map is updated during Phis generation to point to the most recent ----
119 // renaming destination. ----
120 ValueMapTy *VRMapPhi = new ValueMapTy[(MaxStageCount + 1) * 2]; 0
121 ----
122 InstrMapTy InstrMap; 0
123 ----
124 SmallVector PrologBBs; 0
125 ----
126 // Generate the prolog instructions that set up the pipeline. ----
127 generateProlog(MaxStageCount, KernelBB, VRMap, PrologBBs); 0
128 MF.insert(BB->getIterator(), KernelBB); 0
129 ----
130 // Rearrange the instructions to generate the new, pipelined loop, ----
131 // and update register names as needed. ----
132 for (MachineInstr *CI : Schedule.getInstructions()) { 0
133 if (CI->isPHI()) 0
134 continue; 0
135 unsigned StageNum = Schedule.getStage(CI); 0
136 MachineInstr *NewMI = cloneInstr(CI, MaxStageCount, StageNum); 0
137 updateInstruction(NewMI, false, MaxStageCount, StageNum, VRMap); 0
138 KernelBB->push_back(NewMI); 0
139 InstrMap[NewMI] = CI; 0
140 } ----
141 ----
142 // Copy any terminator instructions to the new kernel, and update ----
143 // names as needed. ----
144 for (MachineInstr &MI : BB->terminators()) { 0
145 MachineInstr *NewMI = MF.CloneMachineInstr(&MI); 0
146 updateInstruction(NewMI, false, MaxStageCount, 0, VRMap); 0
147 KernelBB->push_back(NewMI); 0
148 InstrMap[NewMI] = &MI; 0
149 } ----
150 ----
151 NewKernel = KernelBB; 0
152 KernelBB->transferSuccessors(BB); 0
153 KernelBB->replaceSuccessor(BB, KernelBB); 0
154 ----
155 generateExistingPhis(KernelBB, PrologBBs.back(), KernelBB, KernelBB, VRMap, 0
156 InstrMap, MaxStageCount, MaxStageCount, false); ----
157 generatePhis(KernelBB, PrologBBs.back(), KernelBB, KernelBB, VRMap, VRMapPhi, 0
158 InstrMap, MaxStageCount, MaxStageCount, false); ----
159 ----
160 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "New block\n"; KernelBB->dump();); 0
161 ----
162 SmallVector EpilogBBs; 0
163 // Generate the epilog instructions to complete the pipeline. ----
164 generateEpilog(MaxStageCount, KernelBB, BB, VRMap, VRMapPhi, EpilogBBs, 0
165 PrologBBs); ----
166 ----
167 // We need this step because the register allocation doesn't handle some ----
168 // situations well, so we insert copies to help out. ----
169 splitLifetimes(KernelBB, EpilogBBs); 0
170 ----
171 // Remove dead instructions due to loop induction variables. ----
172 removeDeadInstructions(KernelBB, EpilogBBs); 0
173 ----
174 // Add branches between prolog and epilog blocks. ----
175 addBranches(*Preheader, PrologBBs, KernelBB, EpilogBBs, VRMap); 0
176 ----
177 delete[] VRMap; 0
178 delete[] VRMapPhi; 0
179 } 0

181 void ModuloScheduleExpander::cleanup() { 0
182 // Remove the original loop since it's no longer referenced. ----
183 for (auto &I : *BB) 0
184 LIS.RemoveMachineInstrFromMaps(I); 0
185 BB->clear(); 0
186 BB->eraseFromParent(); 0
187 } 0

189 /// Generate the pipeline prolog code. ----
190 void ModuloScheduleExpander::generateProlog(unsigned LastStage, 0
191 MachineBasicBlock *KernelBB, ----
192 ValueMapTy *VRMap, ----
193 MBBVectorTy &PrologBBs) { ----
194 MachineBasicBlock *PredBB = Preheader; 0
195 InstrMapTy InstrMap; 0
196 ----
197 // Generate a basic block for each stage, not including the last stage, ----
198 // which will be generated in the kernel. Each basic block may contain ----
199 // instructions from multiple stages/iterations. ----
200 for (unsigned i = 0; i < LastStage; ++i) { 0
201 // Create and insert the prolog basic block prior to the original loop ----
202 // basic block. The original loop is removed later. ----
203 MachineBasicBlock *NewBB = MF.CreateMachineBasicBlock(BB->getBasicBlock()); 0
204 PrologBBs.push_back(NewBB); 0
205 MF.insert(BB->getIterator(), NewBB); 0
206 NewBB->transferSuccessors(PredBB); 0
207 PredBB->addSuccessor(NewBB); 0
208 PredBB = NewBB; 0
209 ----
210 // Generate instructions for each appropriate stage. Process instructions ----
211 // in original program order. ----
212 for (int StageNum = i; StageNum >= 0; --StageNum) { 0
213 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator BBI = BB->instr_begin(), 0
214 BBE = BB->getFirstTerminator(); 0
215 BBI != BBE; ++BBI) { 0
216 if (Schedule.getStage(&*BBI) == StageNum) { 0
217 if (BBI->isPHI()) 0
218 continue; 0
219 MachineInstr *NewMI = ----
220 cloneAndChangeInstr(&*BBI, i, (unsigned)StageNum); 0
221 updateInstruction(NewMI, false, i, (unsigned)StageNum, VRMap); 0
222 NewBB->push_back(NewMI); 0
223 InstrMap[NewMI] = &*BBI; 0
224 } ----
225 } ----
226 } ----
227 rewritePhiValues(NewBB, i, VRMap, InstrMap); 0
228 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
229 dbgs() << "prolog:\n"; ----
230 NewBB->dump(); ----
231 }); ----
232 } ----
233 ----
234 PredBB->replaceSuccessor(BB, KernelBB); 0
235 ----
236 // Check if we need to remove the branch from the preheader to the original ----
237 // loop, and replace it with a branch to the new loop. ----
238 unsigned numBranches = TII->removeBranch(*Preheader); 0
239 if (numBranches) { 0
240 SmallVector Cond; 0
241 TII->insertBranch(*Preheader, PrologBBs[0], nullptr, Cond, DebugLoc()); 0
242 } 0
243 } 0

245 /// Generate the pipeline epilog code. The epilog code finishes the iterations ----
246 /// that were started in either the prolog or the kernel. We create a basic ----
247 /// block for each stage that needs to complete. ----
248 void ModuloScheduleExpander::generateEpilog( 0
249 unsigned LastStage, MachineBasicBlock *KernelBB, MachineBasicBlock *OrigBB, ----
250 ValueMapTy *VRMap, ValueMapTy *VRMapPhi, MBBVectorTy &EpilogBBs, ----
251 MBBVectorTy &PrologBBs) { ----
252 // We need to change the branch from the kernel to the first epilog block, so ----
253 // this call to analyze branch uses the kernel rather than the original BB. ----
254 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = nullptr, *FBB = nullptr; 0
255 SmallVector Cond; 0
256 bool checkBranch = TII->analyzeBranch(*KernelBB, TBB, FBB, Cond); 0
257 assert(!checkBranch && "generateEpilog must be able to analyze the branch"); 0
258 if (checkBranch) 0
259 return; 0
260 ----
261 MachineBasicBlock::succ_iterator LoopExitI = KernelBB->succ_begin(); 0
262 if (*LoopExitI == KernelBB) 0
263 ++LoopExitI; 0
264 assert(LoopExitI != KernelBB->succ_end() && "Expecting a successor"); 0
265 MachineBasicBlock *LoopExitBB = *LoopExitI; 0
266 ----
267 MachineBasicBlock *PredBB = KernelBB; 0
268 MachineBasicBlock *EpilogStart = LoopExitBB; 0
269 InstrMapTy InstrMap; 0
270 ----
271 // Generate a basic block for each stage, not including the last stage, ----
272 // which was generated for the kernel. Each basic block may contain ----
273 // instructions from multiple stages/iterations. ----
274 int EpilogStage = LastStage + 1; 0
275 for (unsigned i = LastStage; i >= 1; --i, ++EpilogStage) { 0
276 MachineBasicBlock *NewBB = MF.CreateMachineBasicBlock(); 0
277 EpilogBBs.push_back(NewBB); 0
278 MF.insert(BB->getIterator(), NewBB); 0
279 ----
280 PredBB->replaceSuccessor(LoopExitBB, NewBB); 0
281 NewBB->addSuccessor(LoopExitBB); 0
282 ----
283 if (EpilogStart == LoopExitBB) 0
284 EpilogStart = NewBB; 0
285 ----
286 // Add instructions to the epilog depending on the current block. ----
287 // Process instructions in original program order. ----
288 for (unsigned StageNum = i; StageNum <= LastStage; ++StageNum) { 0
289 for (auto &BBI : *BB) { 0
290 if (BBI.isPHI()) 0
291 continue; 0
292 MachineInstr *In = &BBI; 0
293 if ((unsigned)Schedule.getStage(In) == StageNum) { 0
294 // Instructions with memoperands in the epilog are updated with ----
295 // conservative values. ----
296 MachineInstr *NewMI = cloneInstr(In, UINT_MAX, 0); 0
297 updateInstruction(NewMI, i == 1, EpilogStage, 0, VRMap); 0
298 NewBB->push_back(NewMI); 0
299 InstrMap[NewMI] = In; 0
300 } ----
301 } ----
302 } ----
303 generateExistingPhis(NewBB, PrologBBs[i - 1], PredBB, KernelBB, VRMap, 0
304 InstrMap, LastStage, EpilogStage, i == 1); ----
305 generatePhis(NewBB, PrologBBs[i - 1], PredBB, KernelBB, VRMap, VRMapPhi, 0
306 InstrMap, LastStage, EpilogStage, i == 1); ----
307 PredBB = NewBB; 0
308 ----
309 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
310 dbgs() << "epilog:\n"; ----
311 NewBB->dump(); ----
312 }); ----
313 } ----
314 ----
315 // Fix any Phi nodes in the loop exit block. ----
316 LoopExitBB->replacePhiUsesWith(BB, PredBB); 0
317 ----
318 // Create a branch to the new epilog from the kernel. ----
319 // Remove the original branch and add a new branch to the epilog. ----
320 TII->removeBranch(*KernelBB); 0
321 assert((OrigBB == TBB || OrigBB == FBB) && 0
322 "Unable to determine looping branch direction"); ----
323 if (OrigBB != TBB) 0
324 TII->insertBranch(*KernelBB, EpilogStart, KernelBB, Cond, DebugLoc()); 0
325 else ----
326 TII->insertBranch(*KernelBB, KernelBB, EpilogStart, Cond, DebugLoc()); 0
327 // Add a branch to the loop exit. ----
328 if (EpilogBBs.size() > 0) { 0
329 MachineBasicBlock *LastEpilogBB = EpilogBBs.back(); 0
330 SmallVector Cond1; 0
331 TII->insertBranch(*LastEpilogBB, LoopExitBB, nullptr, Cond1, DebugLoc()); 0
332 } 0
333 } 0

335 /// Replace all uses of FromReg that appear outside the specified ----
336 /// basic block with ToReg. ----
337 static void replaceRegUsesAfterLoop(unsigned FromReg, unsigned ToReg, 0
338 MachineBasicBlock *MBB, ----
339 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI, ----
340 LiveIntervals &LIS) { ----
341 for (MachineOperand &O : 0
342 llvm::make_early_inc_range(MRI.use_operands(FromReg))) 0
343 if (O.getParent()->getParent() != MBB) 0
344 O.setReg(ToReg); 0
345 if (!LIS.hasInterval(ToReg)) 0
346 LIS.createEmptyInterval(ToReg); 0
347 } 0

349 /// Return true if the register has a use that occurs outside the ----
350 /// specified loop. ----
351 static bool hasUseAfterLoop(unsigned Reg, MachineBasicBlock *BB, 0
352 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) { ----
353 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MRI.use_operands(Reg)) 0
