359 /// Generate Phis for the specific block in the generated pipelined code. ----
360 /// This function looks at the Phis from the original code to guide the ----
361 /// creation of new Phis. ----
362 void ModuloScheduleExpander::generateExistingPhis( 0
363 MachineBasicBlock *NewBB, MachineBasicBlock *BB1, MachineBasicBlock *BB2, ----
364 MachineBasicBlock *KernelBB, ValueMapTy *VRMap, InstrMapTy &InstrMap, ----
365 unsigned LastStageNum, unsigned CurStageNum, bool IsLast) { ----
366 // Compute the stage number for the initial value of the Phi, which ----
367 // comes from the prolog. The prolog to use depends on to which kernel/ ----
368 // epilog that we're adding the Phi. ----
369 unsigned PrologStage = 0; 0
370 unsigned PrevStage = 0; 0
371 bool InKernel = (LastStageNum == CurStageNum); 0
372 if (InKernel) { 0
373 PrologStage = LastStageNum - 1; 0
374 PrevStage = CurStageNum; 0
375 } else { ----
376 PrologStage = LastStageNum - (CurStageNum - LastStageNum); 0
377 PrevStage = LastStageNum + (CurStageNum - LastStageNum) - 1; 0
378 } ----
379 ----
380 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator BBI = BB->instr_begin(), 0
381 BBE = BB->getFirstNonPHI(); 0
382 BBI != BBE; ++BBI) { 0
383 Register Def = BBI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
384 ----
385 unsigned InitVal = 0; 0
386 unsigned LoopVal = 0; 0
387 getPhiRegs(*BBI, BB, InitVal, LoopVal); 0
388 ----
389 unsigned PhiOp1 = 0; 0
390 // The Phi value from the loop body typically is defined in the loop, but ----
391 // not always. So, we need to check if the value is defined in the loop. ----
392 unsigned PhiOp2 = LoopVal; 0
393 if (VRMap[LastStageNum].count(LoopVal)) 0
394 PhiOp2 = VRMap[LastStageNum][LoopVal]; 0
395 ----
396 int StageScheduled = Schedule.getStage(&*BBI); 0
397 int LoopValStage = Schedule.getStage(MRI.getVRegDef(LoopVal)); 0
398 unsigned NumStages = getStagesForReg(Def, CurStageNum); 0
399 if (NumStages == 0) { 0
400 // We don't need to generate a Phi anymore, but we need to rename any uses ----
401 // of the Phi value. ----
402 unsigned NewReg = VRMap[PrevStage][LoopVal]; 0
403 rewriteScheduledInstr(NewBB, InstrMap, CurStageNum, 0, &*BBI, Def, 0
404 InitVal, NewReg); ----
405 if (VRMap[CurStageNum].count(LoopVal)) 0
406 VRMap[CurStageNum][Def] = VRMap[CurStageNum][LoopVal]; 0
407 } ----
408 // Adjust the number of Phis needed depending on the number of prologs left, ----
409 // and the distance from where the Phi is first scheduled. The number of ----
410 // Phis cannot exceed the number of prolog stages. Each stage can ----
411 // potentially define two values. ----
412 unsigned MaxPhis = PrologStage + 2; 0
413 if (!InKernel && (int)PrologStage <= LoopValStage) 0
414 MaxPhis = std::max((int)MaxPhis - (int)LoopValStage, 1); 0
415 unsigned NumPhis = std::min(NumStages, MaxPhis); 0
416 ----
417 unsigned NewReg = 0; 0
418 unsigned AccessStage = (LoopValStage != -1) ? LoopValStage : StageScheduled; 0
419 // In the epilog, we may need to look back one stage to get the correct ----
420 // Phi name, because the epilog and prolog blocks execute the same stage. ----
421 // The correct name is from the previous block only when the Phi has ----
422 // been completely scheduled prior to the epilog, and Phi value is not ----
423 // needed in multiple stages. ----
424 int StageDiff = 0; 0
425 if (!InKernel && StageScheduled >= LoopValStage && AccessStage == 0 && 0
426 NumPhis == 1) ----
427 StageDiff = 1; 0
428 // Adjust the computations below when the phi and the loop definition ----
429 // are scheduled in different stages. ----
430 if (InKernel && LoopValStage != -1 && StageScheduled > LoopValStage) 0
431 StageDiff = StageScheduled - LoopValStage; 0
432 for (unsigned np = 0; np < NumPhis; ++np) { 0
433 // If the Phi hasn't been scheduled, then use the initial Phi operand ----
434 // value. Otherwise, use the scheduled version of the instruction. This ----
435 // is a little complicated when a Phi references another Phi. ----
436 if (np > PrologStage || StageScheduled >= (int)LastStageNum) 0
437 PhiOp1 = InitVal; 0
438 // Check if the Phi has already been scheduled in a prolog stage. ----
439 else if (PrologStage >= AccessStage + StageDiff + np && 0
440 VRMap[PrologStage - StageDiff - np].count(LoopVal) != 0) 0
441 PhiOp1 = VRMap[PrologStage - StageDiff - np][LoopVal]; 0
442 // Check if the Phi has already been scheduled, but the loop instruction ----
443 // is either another Phi, or doesn't occur in the loop. ----
444 else if (PrologStage >= AccessStage + StageDiff + np) { 0
445 // If the Phi references another Phi, we need to examine the other ----
446 // Phi to get the correct value. ----
447 PhiOp1 = LoopVal; 0
448 MachineInstr *InstOp1 = MRI.getVRegDef(PhiOp1); 0
449 int Indirects = 1; 0
450 while (InstOp1 && InstOp1->isPHI() && InstOp1->getParent() == BB) { 0
451 int PhiStage = Schedule.getStage(InstOp1); 0
452 if ((int)(PrologStage - StageDiff - np) < PhiStage + Indirects) 0
453 PhiOp1 = getInitPhiReg(*InstOp1, BB); 0
454 else ----
455 PhiOp1 = getLoopPhiReg(*InstOp1, BB); 0
456 InstOp1 = MRI.getVRegDef(PhiOp1); 0
457 int PhiOpStage = Schedule.getStage(InstOp1); 0
458 int StageAdj = (PhiOpStage != -1 ? PhiStage - PhiOpStage : 0); 0
459 if (PhiOpStage != -1 && PrologStage - StageAdj >= Indirects + np && 0
460 VRMap[PrologStage - StageAdj - Indirects - np].count(PhiOp1)) { 0
461 PhiOp1 = VRMap[PrologStage - StageAdj - Indirects - np][PhiOp1]; 0
462 break; 0
463 } ----
464 ++Indirects; 0
465 } ----
466 } else ----
467 PhiOp1 = InitVal; 0
468 // If this references a generated Phi in the kernel, get the Phi operand ----
469 // from the incoming block. ----
470 if (MachineInstr *InstOp1 = MRI.getVRegDef(PhiOp1)) 0
471 if (InstOp1->isPHI() && InstOp1->getParent() == KernelBB) 0
472 PhiOp1 = getInitPhiReg(*InstOp1, KernelBB); 0
473 ----
474 MachineInstr *PhiInst = MRI.getVRegDef(LoopVal); 0
475 bool LoopDefIsPhi = PhiInst && PhiInst->isPHI(); 0
476 // In the epilog, a map lookup is needed to get the value from the kernel, ----
477 // or previous epilog block. How is does this depends on if the ----
478 // instruction is scheduled in the previous block. ----
479 if (!InKernel) { 0
480 int StageDiffAdj = 0; 0
481 if (LoopValStage != -1 && StageScheduled > LoopValStage) 0
482 StageDiffAdj = StageScheduled - LoopValStage; 0
483 // Use the loop value defined in the kernel, unless the kernel ----
484 // contains the last definition of the Phi. ----
485 if (np == 0 && PrevStage == LastStageNum && 0
486 (StageScheduled != 0 || LoopValStage != 0) && 0
487 VRMap[PrevStage - StageDiffAdj].count(LoopVal)) 0
488 PhiOp2 = VRMap[PrevStage - StageDiffAdj][LoopVal]; 0
489 // Use the value defined by the Phi. We add one because we switch ----
490 // from looking at the loop value to the Phi definition. ----
491 else if (np > 0 && PrevStage == LastStageNum && 0
492 VRMap[PrevStage - np + 1].count(Def)) 0
493 PhiOp2 = VRMap[PrevStage - np + 1][Def]; 0
494 // Use the loop value defined in the kernel. ----
495 else if (static_cast(LoopValStage) > PrologStage + 1 && 0
496 VRMap[PrevStage - StageDiffAdj - np].count(LoopVal)) 0
497 PhiOp2 = VRMap[PrevStage - StageDiffAdj - np][LoopVal]; 0
498 // Use the value defined by the Phi, unless we're generating the first ----
499 // epilog and the Phi refers to a Phi in a different stage. ----
500 else if (VRMap[PrevStage - np].count(Def) && 0
501 (!LoopDefIsPhi || (PrevStage != LastStageNum) || 0
502 (LoopValStage == StageScheduled))) ----
503 PhiOp2 = VRMap[PrevStage - np][Def]; 0
504 } ----
505 ----
506 // Check if we can reuse an existing Phi. This occurs when a Phi ----
507 // references another Phi, and the other Phi is scheduled in an ----
508 // earlier stage. We can try to reuse an existing Phi up until the last ----
509 // stage of the current Phi. ----
510 if (LoopDefIsPhi) { 0
511 if (static_cast(PrologStage - np) >= StageScheduled) { 0
512 int LVNumStages = getStagesForPhi(LoopVal); 0
513 int StageDiff = (StageScheduled - LoopValStage); 0
514 LVNumStages -= StageDiff; 0
515 // Make sure the loop value Phi has been processed already. ----
516 if (LVNumStages > (int)np && VRMap[CurStageNum].count(LoopVal)) { 0
517 NewReg = PhiOp2; 0
518 unsigned ReuseStage = CurStageNum; 0
519 if (isLoopCarried(*PhiInst)) 0
520 ReuseStage -= LVNumStages; 0
521 // Check if the Phi to reuse has been generated yet. If not, then ----
522 // there is nothing to reuse. ----
523 if (VRMap[ReuseStage - np].count(LoopVal)) { 0
524 NewReg = VRMap[ReuseStage - np][LoopVal]; 0
525 ----
526 rewriteScheduledInstr(NewBB, InstrMap, CurStageNum, np, &*BBI, 0
527 Def, NewReg); ----
528 // Update the map with the new Phi name. ----
529 VRMap[CurStageNum - np][Def] = NewReg; 0
530 PhiOp2 = NewReg; 0
531 if (VRMap[LastStageNum - np - 1].count(LoopVal)) 0
532 PhiOp2 = VRMap[LastStageNum - np - 1][LoopVal]; 0
533 ----
534 if (IsLast && np == NumPhis - 1) 0
535 replaceRegUsesAfterLoop(Def, NewReg, BB, MRI, LIS); 0
536 continue; 0
537 } ----
538 } ----
539 } ----
540 if (InKernel && StageDiff > 0 && 0
541 VRMap[CurStageNum - StageDiff - np].count(LoopVal)) 0
542 PhiOp2 = VRMap[CurStageNum - StageDiff - np][LoopVal]; 0
543 } ----
544 ----
545 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI.getRegClass(Def); 0
546 NewReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
547 ----
548 MachineInstrBuilder NewPhi = ----
549 BuildMI(*NewBB, NewBB->getFirstNonPHI(), DebugLoc(), 0
550 TII->get(TargetOpcode::PHI), NewReg); 0
551 NewPhi.addReg(PhiOp1).addMBB(BB1); 0
552 NewPhi.addReg(PhiOp2).addMBB(BB2); 0
553 if (np == 0) 0
554 InstrMap[NewPhi] = &*BBI; 0
555 ----
556 // We define the Phis after creating the new pipelined code, so ----
557 // we need to rename the Phi values in scheduled instructions. ----
558 ----
559 unsigned PrevReg = 0; 0
560 if (InKernel && VRMap[PrevStage - np].count(LoopVal)) 0
561 PrevReg = VRMap[PrevStage - np][LoopVal]; 0
562 rewriteScheduledInstr(NewBB, InstrMap, CurStageNum, np, &*BBI, Def, 0
563 NewReg, PrevReg); ----
564 // If the Phi has been scheduled, use the new name for rewriting. ----
565 if (VRMap[CurStageNum - np].count(Def)) { 0
566 unsigned R = VRMap[CurStageNum - np][Def]; 0
567 rewriteScheduledInstr(NewBB, InstrMap, CurStageNum, np, &*BBI, R, 0
568 NewReg); ----
569 } ----
570 ----
571 // Check if we need to rename any uses that occurs after the loop. The ----
572 // register to replace depends on whether the Phi is scheduled in the ----
573 // epilog. ----
574 if (IsLast && np == NumPhis - 1) 0
575 replaceRegUsesAfterLoop(Def, NewReg, BB, MRI, LIS); 0
576 ----
577 // In the kernel, a dependent Phi uses the value from this Phi. ----
578 if (InKernel) 0
579 PhiOp2 = NewReg; 0
580 ----
581 // Update the map with the new Phi name. ----
582 VRMap[CurStageNum - np][Def] = NewReg; 0
583 } ----
584 ----
585 while (NumPhis++ < NumStages) { 0
586 rewriteScheduledInstr(NewBB, InstrMap, CurStageNum, NumPhis, &*BBI, Def, 0
587 NewReg, 0); ----
588 } ----
589 ----
590 // Check if we need to rename a Phi that has been eliminated due to ----
591 // scheduling. ----
592 if (NumStages == 0 && IsLast && VRMap[CurStageNum].count(LoopVal)) 0
593 replaceRegUsesAfterLoop(Def, VRMap[CurStageNum][LoopVal], BB, MRI, LIS); 0
594 } ----
595 } 0
596 ----
597 /// Generate Phis for the specified block in the generated pipelined code. ----
598 /// These are new Phis needed because the definition is scheduled after the ----
599 /// use in the pipelined sequence. ----
600 void ModuloScheduleExpander::generatePhis( 0
601 MachineBasicBlock *NewBB, MachineBasicBlock *BB1, MachineBasicBlock *BB2, ----
602 MachineBasicBlock *KernelBB, ValueMapTy *VRMap, ValueMapTy *VRMapPhi, ----
603 InstrMapTy &InstrMap, unsigned LastStageNum, unsigned CurStageNum, ----
604 bool IsLast) { ----
605 // Compute the stage number that contains the initial Phi value, and ----
606 // the Phi from the previous stage. ----
607 unsigned PrologStage = 0; 0
608 unsigned PrevStage = 0; 0
609 unsigned StageDiff = CurStageNum - LastStageNum; 0
610 bool InKernel = (StageDiff == 0); 0
611 if (InKernel) { 0
612 PrologStage = LastStageNum - 1; 0
613 PrevStage = CurStageNum; 0
614 } else { ----
615 PrologStage = LastStageNum - StageDiff; 0
616 PrevStage = LastStageNum + StageDiff - 1; 0
617 } ----
618 ----
619 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator BBI = BB->getFirstNonPHI(), 0
620 BBE = BB->instr_end(); 0
621 BBI != BBE; ++BBI) { 0
622 for (unsigned i = 0, e = BBI->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
623 MachineOperand &MO = BBI->getOperand(i); 0
624 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.isDef() || !MO.getReg().isVirtual()) 0
625 continue; 0
626 ----
627 int StageScheduled = Schedule.getStage(&*BBI); 0
628 assert(StageScheduled != -1 && "Expecting scheduled instruction."); 0
629 Register Def = MO.getReg(); 0
630 unsigned NumPhis = getStagesForReg(Def, CurStageNum); 0
631 // An instruction scheduled in stage 0 and is used after the loop ----
632 // requires a phi in the epilog for the last definition from either ----
633 // the kernel or prolog. ----
634 if (!InKernel && NumPhis == 0 && StageScheduled == 0 && 0
635 hasUseAfterLoop(Def, BB, MRI)) 0
636 NumPhis = 1; 0
637 if (!InKernel && (unsigned)StageScheduled > PrologStage) 0
638 continue; 0
639 ----
640 unsigned PhiOp2; ----
641 if (InKernel) { 0
642 PhiOp2 = VRMap[PrevStage][Def]; 0
643 if (MachineInstr *InstOp2 = MRI.getVRegDef(PhiOp2)) 0
644 if (InstOp2->isPHI() && InstOp2->getParent() == NewBB) 0
645 PhiOp2 = getLoopPhiReg(*InstOp2, BB2); 0
646 } ----
647 // The number of Phis can't exceed the number of prolog stages. The ----
648 // prolog stage number is zero based. ----
649 if (NumPhis > PrologStage + 1 - StageScheduled) 0
650 NumPhis = PrologStage + 1 - StageScheduled; 0
651 for (unsigned np = 0; np < NumPhis; ++np) { 0
652 // Example for ----
653 // Org: ----
654 // %Org = ... (Scheduled at Stage#0, NumPhi = 2) ----
655 // ----
656 // Prolog0 (Stage0): ----
657 // %Clone0 = ... ----
658 // Prolog1 (Stage1): ----
659 // %Clone1 = ... ----
660 // Kernel (Stage2): ----
661 // %Phi0 = Phi %Clone1, Prolog1, %Clone2, Kernel ----
662 // %Phi1 = Phi %Clone0, Prolog1, %Phi0, Kernel ----
663 // %Clone2 = ... ----
664 // Epilog0 (Stage3): ----
665 // %Phi2 = Phi %Clone1, Prolog1, %Clone2, Kernel ----
666 // %Phi3 = Phi %Clone0, Prolog1, %Phi0, Kernel ----
667 // Epilog1 (Stage4): ----
668 // %Phi4 = Phi %Clone0, Prolog0, %Phi2, Epilog0 ----
669 // ----
670 // VRMap = {0: %Clone0, 1: %Clone1, 2: %Clone2} ----
671 // VRMapPhi (after Kernel) = {0: %Phi1, 1: %Phi0} ----
672 // VRMapPhi (after Epilog0) = {0: %Phi3, 1: %Phi2} ----
673 ----
674 unsigned PhiOp1 = VRMap[PrologStage][Def]; 0
675 if (np <= PrologStage) 0
676 PhiOp1 = VRMap[PrologStage - np][Def]; 0
677 if (!InKernel) { 0
678 if (PrevStage == LastStageNum && np == 0) 0
679 PhiOp2 = VRMap[LastStageNum][Def]; 0
680 else ----
681 PhiOp2 = VRMapPhi[PrevStage - np][Def]; 0
682 } ----
683 ----
684 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI.getRegClass(Def); 0
685 Register NewReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
686 ----
687 MachineInstrBuilder NewPhi = ----
688 BuildMI(*NewBB, NewBB->getFirstNonPHI(), DebugLoc(), 0
689 TII->get(TargetOpcode::PHI), NewReg); 0
690 NewPhi.addReg(PhiOp1).addMBB(BB1); 0
691 NewPhi.addReg(PhiOp2).addMBB(BB2); 0
692 if (np == 0) 0
693 InstrMap[NewPhi] = &*BBI; 0
694 ----
695 // Rewrite uses and update the map. The actions depend upon whether ----
696 // we generating code for the kernel or epilog blocks. ----
697 if (InKernel) { 0
698 rewriteScheduledInstr(NewBB, InstrMap, CurStageNum, np, &*BBI, PhiOp1, 0
699 NewReg); ----
700 rewriteScheduledInstr(NewBB, InstrMap, CurStageNum, np, &*BBI, PhiOp2, 0
701 NewReg); ----
702 ----
703 PhiOp2 = NewReg; 0
704 VRMapPhi[PrevStage - np - 1][Def] = NewReg; 0
705 } else { ----
706 VRMapPhi[CurStageNum - np][Def] = NewReg; 0
707 if (np == NumPhis - 1) 0
708 rewriteScheduledInstr(NewBB, InstrMap, CurStageNum, np, &*BBI, Def, 0
709 NewReg); ----
710 } ----
711 if (IsLast && np == NumPhis - 1) 0
712 replaceRegUsesAfterLoop(Def, NewReg, BB, MRI, LIS); 0
713 } ----
714 } ----
715 } ----
716 } 0
717 ----
718 /// Remove instructions that generate values with no uses. ----
719 /// Typically, these are induction variable operations that generate values ----
720 /// used in the loop itself. A dead instruction has a definition with ----
721 /// no uses, or uses that occur in the original loop only. ----
722 void ModuloScheduleExpander::removeDeadInstructions(MachineBasicBlock *KernelBB, 0
723 MBBVectorTy &EpilogBBs) { ----
724 // For each epilog block, check that the value defined by each instruction ----
725 // is used. If not, delete it. ----
726 for (MachineBasicBlock *MBB : llvm::reverse(EpilogBBs)) 0
727 for (MachineBasicBlock::reverse_instr_iterator MI = MBB->instr_rbegin(), 0
728 ME = MBB->instr_rend(); 0
729 MI != ME;) { 0
730 // From DeadMachineInstructionElem. Don't delete inline assembly. ----
731 if (MI->isInlineAsm()) { 0
732 ++MI; 0
733 continue; 0
734 } ----
735 bool SawStore = false; 0
736 // Check if it's safe to remove the instruction due to side effects. ----
737 // We can, and want to, remove Phis here. ----
738 if (!MI->isSafeToMove(nullptr, SawStore) && !MI->isPHI()) { 0
739 ++MI; 0
740 continue; 0
741 } ----
742 bool used = true; 0
743 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI->all_defs()) { 0
744 Register reg = MO.getReg(); 0
745 // Assume physical registers are used, unless they are marked dead. ----
746 if (reg.isPhysical()) { 0
747 used = !MO.isDead(); 0
748 if (used) 0
749 break; 0
750 continue; 0
751 } ----
752 unsigned realUses = 0; 0
753 for (const MachineOperand &U : MRI.use_operands(reg)) { 0
754 // Check if there are any uses that occur only in the original ----
755 // loop. If so, that's not a real use. ----
756 if (U.getParent()->getParent() != BB) { 0
757 realUses++; 0
758 used = true; 0
759 break; 0
760 } ----
761 } ----
762 if (realUses > 0) 0
763 break; 0
764 used = false; 0
765 } ----
766 if (!used) { 0
767 LIS.RemoveMachineInstrFromMaps(*MI); 0
768 MI++->eraseFromParent(); 0
769 continue; 0
770 } ----
771 ++MI; 0
772 } ----
773 // In the kernel block, check if we can remove a Phi that generates a value ----
774 // used in an instruction removed in the epilog block. ----
775 for (MachineInstr &MI : llvm::make_early_inc_range(KernelBB->phis())) { 0
776 Register reg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
777 if (MRI.use_begin(reg) == MRI.use_end()) { 0
778 LIS.RemoveMachineInstrFromMaps(MI); 0
779 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
780 } ----
781 } ----
782 } 0
783 ----
784 /// For loop carried definitions, we split the lifetime of a virtual register ----
785 /// that has uses past the definition in the next iteration. A copy with a new ----
786 /// virtual register is inserted before the definition, which helps with ----
787 /// generating a better register assignment. ----
788 /// ----
789 /// v1 = phi(a, v2) v1 = phi(a, v2) ----
790 /// v2 = phi(b, v3) v2 = phi(b, v3) ----
791 /// v3 = .. v4 = copy v1 ----
792 /// .. = V1 v3 = .. ----
793 /// .. = v4 ----
794 void ModuloScheduleExpander::splitLifetimes(MachineBasicBlock *KernelBB, 0
795 MBBVectorTy &EpilogBBs) { ----
796 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
797 for (auto &PHI : KernelBB->phis()) { 0
798 Register Def = PHI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
799 // Check for any Phi definition that used as an operand of another Phi ----
800 // in the same block. ----
801 for (MachineRegisterInfo::use_instr_iterator I = MRI.use_instr_begin(Def), 0
802 E = MRI.use_instr_end(); 0
803 I != E; ++I) { 0
804 if (I->isPHI() && I->getParent() == KernelBB) { 0
805 // Get the loop carried definition. ----
806 unsigned LCDef = getLoopPhiReg(PHI, KernelBB); 0
807 if (!LCDef) 0
808 continue; 0
809 MachineInstr *MI = MRI.getVRegDef(LCDef); 0
810 if (!MI || MI->getParent() != KernelBB || MI->isPHI()) 0
811 continue; 0
812 // Search through the rest of the block looking for uses of the Phi ----
813 // definition. If one occurs, then split the lifetime. ----
814 unsigned SplitReg = 0; 0
815 for (auto &BBJ : make_range(MachineBasicBlock::instr_iterator(MI), 0
816 KernelBB->instr_end())) 0
817 if (BBJ.readsRegister(Def)) { 0
818 // We split the lifetime when we find the first use. ----
819 if (SplitReg == 0) { 0
820 SplitReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(MRI.getRegClass(Def)); 0
821 BuildMI(*KernelBB, MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), 0
822 TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY), SplitReg) 0
823 .addReg(Def); 0
824 } ----
825 BBJ.substituteRegister(Def, SplitReg, 0, *TRI); 0
826 } ----
827 if (!SplitReg) 0
828 continue; 0
829 // Search through each of the epilog blocks for any uses to be renamed. ----
830 for (auto &Epilog : EpilogBBs) 0
831 for (auto &I : *Epilog) 0
832 if (I.readsRegister(Def)) 0
833 I.substituteRegister(Def, SplitReg, 0, *TRI); 0
834 break; 0
835 } ----
836 } ----
837 } ----
838 } 0
839 ----
840 /// Remove the incoming block from the Phis in a basic block. ----
841 static void removePhis(MachineBasicBlock *BB, MachineBasicBlock *Incoming) { 0
842 for (MachineInstr &MI : *BB) { 0
843 if (!MI.isPHI()) 0
844 break; 0
845 for (unsigned i = 1, e = MI.getNumOperands(); i != e; i += 2) 0
846 if (MI.getOperand(i + 1).getMBB() == Incoming) { 0
847 MI.removeOperand(i + 1); 0
848 MI.removeOperand(i); 0
849 break; 0
850 } ----
851 } ----
852 } 0
853 ----
854 /// Create branches from each prolog basic block to the appropriate epilog ----
855 /// block. These edges are needed if the loop ends before reaching the ----
856 /// kernel. ----
857 void ModuloScheduleExpander::addBranches(MachineBasicBlock &PreheaderBB, 0
858 MBBVectorTy &PrologBBs, ----
859 MachineBasicBlock *KernelBB, ----
860 MBBVectorTy &EpilogBBs, ----
861 ValueMapTy *VRMap) { ----
862 assert(PrologBBs.size() == EpilogBBs.size() && "Prolog/Epilog mismatch"); 0
863 MachineBasicBlock *LastPro = KernelBB; 0
864 MachineBasicBlock *LastEpi = KernelBB; 0
865 ----
866 // Start from the blocks connected to the kernel and work "out" ----
867 // to the first prolog and the last epilog blocks. ----
868 SmallVector PrevInsts; 0
869 unsigned MaxIter = PrologBBs.size() - 1; 0
870 for (unsigned i = 0, j = MaxIter; i <= MaxIter; ++i, --j) { 0
871 // Add branches to the prolog that go to the corresponding ----
872 // epilog, and the fall-thru prolog/kernel block. ----
873 MachineBasicBlock *Prolog = PrologBBs[j]; 0
874 MachineBasicBlock *Epilog = EpilogBBs[i]; 0
875 ----
876 SmallVector Cond; 0
877 std::optional StaticallyGreater = ----
878 LoopInfo->createTripCountGreaterCondition(j + 1, *Prolog, Cond); 0
879 unsigned numAdded = 0; 0
880 if (!StaticallyGreater) { 0
881 Prolog->addSuccessor(Epilog); 0
882 numAdded = TII->insertBranch(*Prolog, Epilog, LastPro, Cond, DebugLoc()); 0
883 } else if (*StaticallyGreater == false) { 0
884 Prolog->addSuccessor(Epilog); 0
885 Prolog->removeSuccessor(LastPro); 0
886 LastEpi->removeSuccessor(Epilog); 0
887 numAdded = TII->insertBranch(*Prolog, Epilog, nullptr, Cond, DebugLoc()); 0
888 removePhis(Epilog, LastEpi); 0
889 // Remove the blocks that are no longer referenced. ----
890 if (LastPro != LastEpi) { 0
891 LastEpi->clear(); 0
892 LastEpi->eraseFromParent(); 0
893 } ----
894 if (LastPro == KernelBB) { 0
895 LoopInfo->disposed(); 0
896 NewKernel = nullptr; 0
897 } ----
898 LastPro->clear(); 0
899 LastPro->eraseFromParent(); 0
900 } else { ----
901 numAdded = TII->insertBranch(*Prolog, LastPro, nullptr, Cond, DebugLoc()); 0
902 removePhis(Epilog, Prolog); 0
903 } ----
904 LastPro = Prolog; 0
905 LastEpi = Epilog; 0
906 for (MachineBasicBlock::reverse_instr_iterator I = Prolog->instr_rbegin(), 0
907 E = Prolog->instr_rend(); 0
908 I != E && numAdded > 0; ++I, --numAdded) 0
909 updateInstruction(&*I, false, j, 0, VRMap); 0
910 } 0
911 ----
912 if (NewKernel) { 0
913 LoopInfo->setPreheader(PrologBBs[MaxIter]); 0
914 LoopInfo->adjustTripCount(-(MaxIter + 1)); 0
915 } ----
916 } 0
917 ----
918 /// Return true if we can compute the amount the instruction changes ----
919 /// during each iteration. Set Delta to the amount of the change. ----
920 bool ModuloScheduleExpander::computeDelta(MachineInstr &MI, unsigned &Delta) { 0
921 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
922 const MachineOperand *BaseOp; ----
923 int64_t Offset; ----
924 bool OffsetIsScalable; ----
925 if (!TII->getMemOperandWithOffset(MI, BaseOp, Offset, OffsetIsScalable, TRI)) 0
926 return false; 0
927 ----
928 // FIXME: This algorithm assumes instructions have fixed-size offsets. ----
929 if (OffsetIsScalable) 0
930 return false; 0
931 ----
932 if (!BaseOp->isReg()) 0
933 return false; 0
934 ----
935 Register BaseReg = BaseOp->getReg(); 0
936 ----
937 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo(); 0
938 // Check if there is a Phi. If so, get the definition in the loop. ----
939 MachineInstr *BaseDef = MRI.getVRegDef(BaseReg); 0
940 if (BaseDef && BaseDef->isPHI()) { 0
941 BaseReg = getLoopPhiReg(*BaseDef, MI.getParent()); 0
942 BaseDef = MRI.getVRegDef(BaseReg); 0
943 } ----
944 if (!BaseDef) 0
945 return false; 0
946 ----
947 int D = 0; 0
948 if (!TII->getIncrementValue(*BaseDef, D) && D >= 0) 0
949 return false; 0
950 ----
951 Delta = D; 0
952 return true; 0
953 } ----
954 ----
955 /// Update the memory operand with a new offset when the pipeliner ----
956 /// generates a new copy of the instruction that refers to a ----
957 /// different memory location. ----
958 void ModuloScheduleExpander::updateMemOperands(MachineInstr &NewMI, 0
959 MachineInstr &OldMI, ----
960 unsigned Num) { ----
961 if (Num == 0) 0
962 return; 0
963 // If the instruction has memory operands, then adjust the offset ----
964 // when the instruction appears in different stages. ----
965 if (NewMI.memoperands_empty()) 0
966 return; 0
967 SmallVector NewMMOs; 0
968 for (MachineMemOperand *MMO : NewMI.memoperands()) { 0
969 // TODO: Figure out whether isAtomic is really necessary (see D57601). ----
970 if (MMO->isVolatile() || MMO->isAtomic() || 0
971 (MMO->isInvariant() && MMO->isDereferenceable()) || 0
972 (!MMO->getValue())) { 0
973 NewMMOs.push_back(MMO); 0
974 continue; 0
975 } ----
976 unsigned Delta; ----
977 if (Num != UINT_MAX && computeDelta(OldMI, Delta)) { 0
978 int64_t AdjOffset = Delta * Num; 0
979 NewMMOs.push_back( 0
980 MF.getMachineMemOperand(MMO, AdjOffset, MMO->getSize())); 0
981 } else { ----
982 NewMMOs.push_back( 0
983 MF.getMachineMemOperand(MMO, 0, MemoryLocation::UnknownSize)); 0
984 } ----
985 } ----
986 NewMI.setMemRefs(MF, NewMMOs); 0
987 } 0
988 ----
989 /// Clone the instruction for the new pipelined loop and update the ----
990 /// memory operands, if needed. ----
991 MachineInstr *ModuloScheduleExpander::cloneInstr(MachineInstr *OldMI, 0
992 unsigned CurStageNum, ----
993 unsigned InstStageNum) { ----
994 MachineInstr *NewMI = MF.CloneMachineInstr(OldMI); 0
995 updateMemOperands(*NewMI, *OldMI, CurStageNum - InstStageNum); 0
996 return NewMI; 0
997 } ----
998 ----
999 /// Clone the instruction for the new pipelined loop. If needed, this ----
1000 /// function updates the instruction using the values saved in the ----
1001 /// InstrChanges structure. ----
1002 MachineInstr *ModuloScheduleExpander::cloneAndChangeInstr( 0
1003 MachineInstr *OldMI, unsigned CurStageNum, unsigned InstStageNum) { ----
1004 MachineInstr *NewMI = MF.CloneMachineInstr(OldMI); 0
1005 auto It = InstrChanges.find(OldMI); 0
1006 if (It != InstrChanges.end()) { 0
1007 std::pair RegAndOffset = It->second; 0
1008 unsigned BasePos, OffsetPos; ----
1009 if (!TII->getBaseAndOffsetPosition(*OldMI, BasePos, OffsetPos)) 0
1010 return nullptr; 0
1011 int64_t NewOffset = OldMI->getOperand(OffsetPos).getImm(); 0
1012 MachineInstr *LoopDef = findDefInLoop(RegAndOffset.first); 0
1013 if (Schedule.getStage(LoopDef) > (signed)InstStageNum) 0
1014 NewOffset += RegAndOffset.second * (CurStageNum - InstStageNum); 0
1015 NewMI->getOperand(OffsetPos).setImm(NewOffset); 0
1016 } ----
1017 updateMemOperands(*NewMI, *OldMI, CurStageNum - InstStageNum); 0
1018 return NewMI; 0
1019 } ----
1020 ----
1021 /// Update the machine instruction with new virtual registers. This ----
1022 /// function may change the definitions and/or uses. ----
1023 void ModuloScheduleExpander::updateInstruction(MachineInstr *NewMI, 0
1024 bool LastDef, ----
1025 unsigned CurStageNum, ----
1026 unsigned InstrStageNum, ----
1027 ValueMapTy *VRMap) { ----
1028 for (MachineOperand &MO : NewMI->operands()) { 0
1029 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.getReg().isVirtual()) 0
1030 continue; 0
1031 Register reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1032 if (MO.isDef()) { 0
1033 // Create a new virtual register for the definition. ----
1034 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI.getRegClass(reg); 0
1035 Register NewReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1036 MO.setReg(NewReg); 0
1037 VRMap[CurStageNum][reg] = NewReg; 0
1038 if (LastDef) 0
1039 replaceRegUsesAfterLoop(reg, NewReg, BB, MRI, LIS); 0
1040 } else if (MO.isUse()) { 0
1041 MachineInstr *Def = MRI.getVRegDef(reg); 0
1042 // Compute the stage that contains the last definition for instruction. ----
1043 int DefStageNum = Schedule.getStage(Def); 0
1044 unsigned StageNum = CurStageNum; 0
1045 if (DefStageNum != -1 && (int)InstrStageNum > DefStageNum) { 0
1046 // Compute the difference in stages between the defintion and the use. ----
1047 unsigned StageDiff = (InstrStageNum - DefStageNum); 0
1048 // Make an adjustment to get the last definition. ----
1049 StageNum -= StageDiff; 0
1050 } ----
1051 if (VRMap[StageNum].count(reg)) 0
1052 MO.setReg(VRMap[StageNum][reg]); 0
1053 } ----
1054 } ----
1055 } 0
1056 ----
1057 /// Return the instruction in the loop that defines the register. ----
1058 /// If the definition is a Phi, then follow the Phi operand to ----
1059 /// the instruction in the loop. ----
1060 MachineInstr *ModuloScheduleExpander::findDefInLoop(unsigned Reg) { 0
1061 SmallPtrSet Visited; 0
1062 MachineInstr *Def = MRI.getVRegDef(Reg); 0
1063 while (Def->isPHI()) { 0
1064 if (!Visited.insert(Def).second) 0
1065 break; 0
1066 for (unsigned i = 1, e = Def->getNumOperands(); i < e; i += 2) 0
1067 if (Def->getOperand(i + 1).getMBB() == BB) { 0
1068 Def = MRI.getVRegDef(Def->getOperand(i).getReg()); 0
1069 break; 0
1070 } ----
1071 } ----
1072 return Def; 0
1073 } 0
1074 ----
1075 /// Return the new name for the value from the previous stage. ----
1076 unsigned ModuloScheduleExpander::getPrevMapVal( 0
1077 unsigned StageNum, unsigned PhiStage, unsigned LoopVal, unsigned LoopStage, ----
1078 ValueMapTy *VRMap, MachineBasicBlock *BB) { ----
1079 unsigned PrevVal = 0; 0
1080 if (StageNum > PhiStage) { 0
1081 MachineInstr *LoopInst = MRI.getVRegDef(LoopVal); 0
1082 if (PhiStage == LoopStage && VRMap[StageNum - 1].count(LoopVal)) 0
1083 // The name is defined in the previous stage. ----
1084 PrevVal = VRMap[StageNum - 1][LoopVal]; 0
1085 else if (VRMap[StageNum].count(LoopVal)) 0
1086 // The previous name is defined in the current stage when the instruction ----
1087 // order is swapped. ----
1088 PrevVal = VRMap[StageNum][LoopVal]; 0
1089 else if (!LoopInst->isPHI() || LoopInst->getParent() != BB) 0
1090 // The loop value hasn't yet been scheduled. ----
1091 PrevVal = LoopVal; 0
1092 else if (StageNum == PhiStage + 1) 0
1093 // The loop value is another phi, which has not been scheduled. ----
1094 PrevVal = getInitPhiReg(*LoopInst, BB); 0
1095 else if (StageNum > PhiStage + 1 && LoopInst->getParent() == BB) 0
1096 // The loop value is another phi, which has been scheduled. ----
1097 PrevVal = ----
1098 getPrevMapVal(StageNum - 1, PhiStage, getLoopPhiReg(*LoopInst, BB), 0
1099 LoopStage, VRMap, BB); ----
1100 } ----
1101 return PrevVal; 0
1102 } ----
1103 ----
1104 /// Rewrite the Phi values in the specified block to use the mappings ----
1105 /// from the initial operand. Once the Phi is scheduled, we switch ----
1106 /// to using the loop value instead of the Phi value, so those names ----
1107 /// do not need to be rewritten. ----
1108 void ModuloScheduleExpander::rewritePhiValues(MachineBasicBlock *NewBB, 0
1109 unsigned StageNum, ----
1110 ValueMapTy *VRMap, ----
1111 InstrMapTy &InstrMap) { ----
1112 for (auto &PHI : BB->phis()) { 0
1113 unsigned InitVal = 0; 0
1114 unsigned LoopVal = 0; 0
1115 getPhiRegs(PHI, BB, InitVal, LoopVal); 0
1116 Register PhiDef = PHI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1117 ----
1118 unsigned PhiStage = (unsigned)Schedule.getStage(MRI.getVRegDef(PhiDef)); 0
1119 unsigned LoopStage = (unsigned)Schedule.getStage(MRI.getVRegDef(LoopVal)); 0
1120 unsigned NumPhis = getStagesForPhi(PhiDef); 0
1121 if (NumPhis > StageNum) 0
1122 NumPhis = StageNum; 0
1123 for (unsigned np = 0; np <= NumPhis; ++np) { 0
1124 unsigned NewVal = ----
1125 getPrevMapVal(StageNum - np, PhiStage, LoopVal, LoopStage, VRMap, BB); 0
1126 if (!NewVal) 0
1127 NewVal = InitVal; 0
1128 rewriteScheduledInstr(NewBB, InstrMap, StageNum - np, np, &PHI, PhiDef, 0
1129 NewVal); ----
1130 } ----
1131 } ----
1132 } 0
1133 ----
1134 /// Rewrite a previously scheduled instruction to use the register value ----
1135 /// from the new instruction. Make sure the instruction occurs in the ----
1136 /// basic block, and we don't change the uses in the new instruction. ----
1137 void ModuloScheduleExpander::rewriteScheduledInstr( 0
1138 MachineBasicBlock *BB, InstrMapTy &InstrMap, unsigned CurStageNum, ----
1139 unsigned PhiNum, MachineInstr *Phi, unsigned OldReg, unsigned NewReg, ----
1140 unsigned PrevReg) { ----
1141 bool InProlog = (CurStageNum < (unsigned)Schedule.getNumStages() - 1); 0
1142 int StagePhi = Schedule.getStage(Phi) + PhiNum; 0
1143 // Rewrite uses that have been scheduled already to use the new ----
1144 // Phi register. ----
1145 for (MachineOperand &UseOp : 0
1146 llvm::make_early_inc_range(MRI.use_operands(OldReg))) { 0
1147 MachineInstr *UseMI = UseOp.getParent(); 0
1148 if (UseMI->getParent() != BB) 0
1149 continue; 0
1150 if (UseMI->isPHI()) { 0
1151 if (!Phi->isPHI() && UseMI->getOperand(0).getReg() == NewReg) 0
1152 continue; 0
1153 if (getLoopPhiReg(*UseMI, BB) != OldReg) 0
1154 continue; 0
1155 } ----
1156 InstrMapTy::iterator OrigInstr = InstrMap.find(UseMI); 0
1157 assert(OrigInstr != InstrMap.end() && "Instruction not scheduled."); 0
1158 MachineInstr *OrigMI = OrigInstr->second; 0
1159 int StageSched = Schedule.getStage(OrigMI); 0
1160 int CycleSched = Schedule.getCycle(OrigMI); 0
1161 unsigned ReplaceReg = 0; 0
1162 // This is the stage for the scheduled instruction. ----
1163 if (StagePhi == StageSched && Phi->isPHI()) { 0
1164 int CyclePhi = Schedule.getCycle(Phi); 0
1165 if (PrevReg && InProlog) 0
1166 ReplaceReg = PrevReg; 0
1167 else if (PrevReg && !isLoopCarried(*Phi) && 0
1168 (CyclePhi <= CycleSched || OrigMI->isPHI())) 0
1169 ReplaceReg = PrevReg; 0
1170 else ----
1171 ReplaceReg = NewReg; 0
1172 } ----
1173 // The scheduled instruction occurs before the scheduled Phi, and the ----
1174 // Phi is not loop carried. ----
1175 if (!InProlog && StagePhi + 1 == StageSched && !isLoopCarried(*Phi)) 0
1176 ReplaceReg = NewReg; 0
1177 if (StagePhi > StageSched && Phi->isPHI()) 0
1178 ReplaceReg = NewReg; 0
1179 if (!InProlog && !Phi->isPHI() && StagePhi < StageSched) 0
1180 ReplaceReg = NewReg; 0
1181 if (ReplaceReg) { 0
1182 const TargetRegisterClass *NRC = ----
1183 MRI.constrainRegClass(ReplaceReg, MRI.getRegClass(OldReg)); 0
1184 if (NRC) 0
1185 UseOp.setReg(ReplaceReg); 0
1186 else { ----
1187 Register SplitReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(MRI.getRegClass(OldReg)); 0
1188 BuildMI(*BB, UseMI, UseMI->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY), 0
1189 SplitReg) ----
1190 .addReg(ReplaceReg); 0
1191 UseOp.setReg(SplitReg); 0
1192 } ----
1193 } ----
1194 } ----
1195 } 0
1196 ----
1197 bool ModuloScheduleExpander::isLoopCarried(MachineInstr &Phi) { 0
1198 if (!Phi.isPHI()) 0
1199 return false; 0
1200 int DefCycle = Schedule.getCycle(&Phi); 0
1201 int DefStage = Schedule.getStage(&Phi); 0
1202 ----
1203 unsigned InitVal = 0; 0
1204 unsigned LoopVal = 0; 0
1205 getPhiRegs(Phi, Phi.getParent(), InitVal, LoopVal); 0
1206 MachineInstr *Use = MRI.getVRegDef(LoopVal); 0
1207 if (!Use || Use->isPHI()) 0
1208 return true; 0
1209 int LoopCycle = Schedule.getCycle(Use); 0
1210 int LoopStage = Schedule.getStage(Use); 0
1211 return (LoopCycle > DefCycle) || (LoopStage <= DefStage); 0
1212 } ----
1213 ----
1214 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1215 // PeelingModuloScheduleExpander implementation ----
1216 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1217 // This is a reimplementation of ModuloScheduleExpander that works by creating ----
1218 // a fully correct steady-state kernel and peeling off the prolog and epilogs. ----
1219 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1220 ----
1221 namespace { ----
1222 // Remove any dead phis in MBB. Dead phis either have only one block as input ----
1223 // (in which case they are the identity) or have no uses. ----
1224 void EliminateDeadPhis(MachineBasicBlock *MBB, MachineRegisterInfo &MRI, 0
1225 LiveIntervals *LIS, bool KeepSingleSrcPhi = false) { ----
1226 bool Changed = true; 0
1227 while (Changed) { 0
1228 Changed = false; 0
1229 for (MachineInstr &MI : llvm::make_early_inc_range(MBB->phis())) { 0
1230 assert(MI.isPHI()); 0
1231 if (MRI.use_empty(MI.getOperand(0).getReg())) { 0
1232 if (LIS) 0
1233 LIS->RemoveMachineInstrFromMaps(MI); 0
1234 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1235 Changed = true; 0
1236 } else if (!KeepSingleSrcPhi && MI.getNumExplicitOperands() == 3) { 0
1237 const TargetRegisterClass *ConstrainRegClass = ----
1238 MRI.constrainRegClass(MI.getOperand(1).getReg(), 0
1239 MRI.getRegClass(MI.getOperand(0).getReg())); 0
1240 assert(ConstrainRegClass && 0
1241 "Expected a valid constrained register class!"); ----
1242 (void)ConstrainRegClass; ----
1243 MRI.replaceRegWith(MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), 0
1244 MI.getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1245 if (LIS) 0
1246 LIS->RemoveMachineInstrFromMaps(MI); 0
1247 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1248 Changed = true; 0
1249 } ----
1250 } ----
1251 } ----
1252 } 0
1253 ----
1254 /// Rewrites the kernel block in-place to adhere to the given schedule. ----
1255 /// KernelRewriter holds all of the state required to perform the rewriting. ----
1256 class KernelRewriter { ----
1257 ModuloSchedule &S; ----
1258 MachineBasicBlock *BB; ----
1259 MachineBasicBlock *PreheaderBB, *ExitBB; ----
1260 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI; ----
1261 const TargetInstrInfo *TII; ----
1262 LiveIntervals *LIS; ----
1263 ----
1264 // Map from register class to canonical undef register for that class. ----
1265 DenseMap Undefs; ----
1266 // Map from to phi register for all created phis. Note that ----
1267 // this map is only used when InitReg is non-undef. ----
1268 DenseMap, Register> Phis; ----
1269 // Map from LoopReg to phi register where the InitReg is undef. ----
1270 DenseMap UndefPhis; ----
1271 ----
1272 // Reg is used by MI. Return the new register MI should use to adhere to the ----
1273 // schedule. Insert phis as necessary. ----
1274 Register remapUse(Register Reg, MachineInstr &MI); ----
1275 // Insert a phi that carries LoopReg from the loop body and InitReg otherwise. ----
1276 // If InitReg is not given it is chosen arbitrarily. It will either be undef ----
1277 // or will be chosen so as to share another phi. ----
1278 Register phi(Register LoopReg, std::optional InitReg = {}, ----
1279 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = nullptr); ----
1280 // Create an undef register of the given register class. ----
1281 Register undef(const TargetRegisterClass *RC); ----
1282 ----
1283 public: ----
1284 KernelRewriter(MachineLoop &L, ModuloSchedule &S, MachineBasicBlock *LoopBB, ----
1285 LiveIntervals *LIS = nullptr); ----
1286 void rewrite(); ----
1287 }; ----
1288 } // namespace ----
1289 ----
1290 KernelRewriter::KernelRewriter(MachineLoop &L, ModuloSchedule &S, 0
1291 MachineBasicBlock *LoopBB, LiveIntervals *LIS) ----
1292 : S(S), BB(LoopBB), PreheaderBB(L.getLoopPreheader()), 0
1293 ExitBB(L.getExitBlock()), MRI(BB->getParent()->getRegInfo()), 0
1294 TII(BB->getParent()->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo()), LIS(LIS) { 0
1295 PreheaderBB = *BB->pred_begin(); 0
1296 if (PreheaderBB == BB) 0
1297 PreheaderBB = *std::next(BB->pred_begin()); 0
1298 } 0
1299 ----
1300 void KernelRewriter::rewrite() { 0
1301 // Rearrange the loop to be in schedule order. Note that the schedule may ----
1302 // contain instructions that are not owned by the loop block (InstrChanges and ----
1303 // friends), so we gracefully handle unowned instructions and delete any ----
1304 // instructions that weren't in the schedule. ----
1305 auto InsertPt = BB->getFirstTerminator(); 0
1306 MachineInstr *FirstMI = nullptr; 0
1307 for (MachineInstr *MI : S.getInstructions()) { 0
1308 if (MI->isPHI()) 0
1309 continue; 0
1310 if (MI->getParent()) 0
1311 MI->removeFromParent(); 0
1312 BB->insert(InsertPt, MI); 0
1313 if (!FirstMI) 0
1314 FirstMI = MI; 0
1315 } ----
1316 assert(FirstMI && "Failed to find first MI in schedule"); 0
1317 ----
1318 // At this point all of the scheduled instructions are between FirstMI ----
1319 // and the end of the block. Kill from the first non-phi to FirstMI. ----
1320 for (auto I = BB->getFirstNonPHI(); I != FirstMI->getIterator();) { 0
1321 if (LIS) 0
1322 LIS->RemoveMachineInstrFromMaps(*I); 0
1323 (I++)->eraseFromParent(); 0
1324 } ----
1325 ----
1326 // Now remap every instruction in the loop. ----
1327 for (MachineInstr &MI : *BB) { 0
1328 if (MI.isPHI() || MI.isTerminator()) 0
1329 continue; 0
1330 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI.uses()) { 0
1331 if (!MO.isReg() || MO.getReg().isPhysical() || MO.isImplicit()) 0
1332 continue; 0
1333 Register Reg = remapUse(MO.getReg(), MI); 0
1334 MO.setReg(Reg); 0
1335 } ----
1336 } ----
1337 EliminateDeadPhis(BB, MRI, LIS); 0
1338 ----
1339 // Ensure a phi exists for all instructions that are either referenced by ----
1340 // an illegal phi or by an instruction outside the loop. This allows us to ----
1341 // treat remaps of these values the same as "normal" values that come from ----
1342 // loop-carried phis. ----
1343 for (auto MI = BB->getFirstNonPHI(); MI != BB->end(); ++MI) { 0
1344 if (MI->isPHI()) { 0
1345 Register R = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1346 phi(R); 0
1347 continue; 0
1348 } 0
1349 ----
1350 for (MachineOperand &Def : MI->defs()) { 0
1351 for (MachineInstr &MI : MRI.use_instructions(Def.getReg())) { 0
1352 if (MI.getParent() != BB) { 0
1353 phi(Def.getReg()); 0
1354 break; 0
1355 } ----
1356 } ----
1357 } ----
1358 } ----
1359 } 0
1360 ----
1361 Register KernelRewriter::remapUse(Register Reg, MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1362 MachineInstr *Producer = MRI.getUniqueVRegDef(Reg); 0
1363 if (!Producer) 0
1364 return Reg; 0
1365 ----
1366 int ConsumerStage = S.getStage(&MI); 0
1367 if (!Producer->isPHI()) { 0
1368 // Non-phi producers are simple to remap. Insert as many phis as the ----
1369 // difference between the consumer and producer stages. ----
1370 if (Producer->getParent() != BB) 0
1371 // Producer was not inside the loop. Use the register as-is. ----
1372 return Reg; 0
1373 int ProducerStage = S.getStage(Producer); 0
1374 assert(ConsumerStage != -1 && 0
1375 "In-loop consumer should always be scheduled!"); ----
1376 assert(ConsumerStage >= ProducerStage); 0
1377 unsigned StageDiff = ConsumerStage - ProducerStage; 0
1378 ----
1379 for (unsigned I = 0; I < StageDiff; ++I) 0
1380 Reg = phi(Reg); 0
1381 return Reg; 0
1382 } ----
1383 ----
1384 // First, dive through the phi chain to find the defaults for the generated ----
1385 // phis. ----
1386 SmallVector, 4> Defaults; 0
1387 Register LoopReg = Reg; 0
1388 auto LoopProducer = Producer; 0
1389 while (LoopProducer->isPHI() && LoopProducer->getParent() == BB) { 0
1390 LoopReg = getLoopPhiReg(*LoopProducer, BB); 0
1391 Defaults.emplace_back(getInitPhiReg(*LoopProducer, BB)); 0
1392 LoopProducer = MRI.getUniqueVRegDef(LoopReg); 0
1393 assert(LoopProducer); 0
1394 } ----
1395 int LoopProducerStage = S.getStage(LoopProducer); 0
1396 ----
1397 std::optional IllegalPhiDefault; 0
1398 ----
1399 if (LoopProducerStage == -1) { 0
1400 // Do nothing. ----
1401 } else if (LoopProducerStage > ConsumerStage) { 0
1402 // This schedule is only representable if ProducerStage == ConsumerStage+1. ----
1403 // In addition, Consumer's cycle must be scheduled after Producer in the ----
1404 // rescheduled loop. This is enforced by the pipeliner's ASAP and ALAP ----
1405 // functions. ----
1406 #ifndef NDEBUG // Silence unused variables in non-asserts mode. ----
1407 int LoopProducerCycle = S.getCycle(LoopProducer); 0
1408 int ConsumerCycle = S.getCycle(&MI); 0
1409 #endif ----
1410 assert(LoopProducerCycle <= ConsumerCycle); 0
1411 assert(LoopProducerStage == ConsumerStage + 1); 0
1412 // Peel off the first phi from Defaults and insert a phi between producer ----
1413 // and consumer. This phi will not be at the front of the block so we ----
1414 // consider it illegal. It will only exist during the rewrite process; it ----
1415 // needs to exist while we peel off prologs because these could take the ----
1416 // default value. After that we can replace all uses with the loop producer ----
1417 // value. ----
1418 IllegalPhiDefault = Defaults.front(); 0
1419 Defaults.erase(Defaults.begin()); 0
1420 } else { ----
1421 assert(ConsumerStage >= LoopProducerStage); 0
1422 int StageDiff = ConsumerStage - LoopProducerStage; 0
1423 if (StageDiff > 0) { 0
1424 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " -- padding defaults array from " << Defaults.size() 0
1425 << " to " << (Defaults.size() + StageDiff) << "\n"); ----
1426 // If we need more phis than we have defaults for, pad out with undefs for ----
1427 // the earliest phis, which are at the end of the defaults chain (the ----
1428 // chain is in reverse order). ----
1429 Defaults.resize(Defaults.size() + StageDiff, 0
1430 Defaults.empty() ? std::optional() 0
1431 : Defaults.back()); 0
1432 } ----
1433 } ----
1434 ----
1435 // Now we know the number of stages to jump back, insert the phi chain. ----
1436 auto DefaultI = Defaults.rbegin(); 0
1437 while (DefaultI != Defaults.rend()) 0
1438 LoopReg = phi(LoopReg, *DefaultI++, MRI.getRegClass(Reg)); 0
1439 ----
1440 if (IllegalPhiDefault) { 0
1441 // The consumer optionally consumes LoopProducer in the same iteration ----
1442 // (because the producer is scheduled at an earlier cycle than the consumer) ----
1443 // or the initial value. To facilitate this we create an illegal block here ----
1444 // by embedding a phi in the middle of the block. We will fix this up ----
1445 // immediately prior to pruning. ----
1446 auto RC = MRI.getRegClass(Reg); 0
1447 Register R = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1448 MachineInstr *IllegalPhi = ----
1449 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DebugLoc(), TII->get(TargetOpcode::PHI), R) 0
1450 .addReg(*IllegalPhiDefault) 0
1451 .addMBB(PreheaderBB) // Block choice is arbitrary and has no effect. 0
1452 .addReg(LoopReg) 0
1453 .addMBB(BB); // Block choice is arbitrary and has no effect. 0
1454 // Illegal phi should belong to the producer stage so that it can be ----
1455 // filtered correctly during peeling. ----
1456 S.setStage(IllegalPhi, LoopProducerStage); 0
1457 return R; 0
1458 } ----
1459 ----
1460 return LoopReg; 0
1461 } 0
1462 ----
1463 Register KernelRewriter::phi(Register LoopReg, std::optional InitReg, 0
1464 const TargetRegisterClass *RC) { ----
1465 // If the init register is not undef, try and find an existing phi. ----
1466 if (InitReg) { 0
1467 auto I = Phis.find({LoopReg, *InitReg}); 0
1468 if (I != Phis.end()) 0
1469 return I->second; 0
1470 } else { ----
1471 for (auto &KV : Phis) { 0
1472 if (KV.first.first == LoopReg) 0
1473 return KV.second; 0
1474 } ----
1475 } ----
1476 ----
1477 // InitReg is either undef or no existing phi takes InitReg as input. Try and ----
1478 // find a phi that takes undef as input. ----
1479 auto I = UndefPhis.find(LoopReg); 0
1480 if (I != UndefPhis.end()) { 0
1481 Register R = I->second; 0
1482 if (!InitReg) 0
1483 // Found a phi taking undef as input, and this input is undef so return ----
1484 // without any more changes. ----
1485 return R; 0
1486 // Found a phi taking undef as input, so rewrite it to take InitReg. ----
1487 MachineInstr *MI = MRI.getVRegDef(R); 0
1488 MI->getOperand(1).setReg(*InitReg); 0
1489 Phis.insert({{LoopReg, *InitReg}, R}); 0
1490 const TargetRegisterClass *ConstrainRegClass = ----
1491 MRI.constrainRegClass(R, MRI.getRegClass(*InitReg)); 0
1492 assert(ConstrainRegClass && "Expected a valid constrained register class!"); 0
1493 (void)ConstrainRegClass; ----
1494 UndefPhis.erase(I); 0
1495 return R; 0
1496 } ----
1497 ----
1498 // Failed to find any existing phi to reuse, so create a new one. ----
1499 if (!RC) 0
1500 RC = MRI.getRegClass(LoopReg); 0
1501 Register R = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1502 if (InitReg) { 0
1503 const TargetRegisterClass *ConstrainRegClass = ----
1504 MRI.constrainRegClass(R, MRI.getRegClass(*InitReg)); 0
1505 assert(ConstrainRegClass && "Expected a valid constrained register class!"); 0
1506 (void)ConstrainRegClass; ----
1507 } ----
1508 BuildMI(*BB, BB->getFirstNonPHI(), DebugLoc(), TII->get(TargetOpcode::PHI), R) 0
1509 .addReg(InitReg ? *InitReg : undef(RC)) 0
1510 .addMBB(PreheaderBB) 0
1511 .addReg(LoopReg) 0
1512 .addMBB(BB); 0
1513 if (!InitReg) 0
1514 UndefPhis[LoopReg] = R; 0
1515 else ----
1516 Phis[{LoopReg, *InitReg}] = R; 0
1517 return R; 0
1518 } ----
1519 ----
1520 Register KernelRewriter::undef(const TargetRegisterClass *RC) { 0
1521 Register &R = Undefs[RC]; 0
1522 if (R == 0) { 0
1523 // Create an IMPLICIT_DEF that defines this register if we need it. ----
1524 // All uses of this should be removed by the time we have finished unrolling ----
1525 // prologs and epilogs. ----
1526 R = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1527 auto *InsertBB = &PreheaderBB->getParent()->front(); 0
1528 BuildMI(*InsertBB, InsertBB->getFirstTerminator(), DebugLoc(), 0
1529 TII->get(TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF), R); 0
1530 } ----
1531 return R; 0
1532 } ----
1533 ----
1534 namespace { ----
1535 /// Describes an operand in the kernel of a pipelined loop. Characteristics of ----
1536 /// the operand are discovered, such as how many in-loop PHIs it has to jump ----
1537 /// through and defaults for these phis. ----
1538 class KernelOperandInfo { ----
1539 MachineBasicBlock *BB; ----
1540 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI; ----
1541 SmallVector PhiDefaults; ----
1542 MachineOperand *Source; ----
1543 MachineOperand *Target; ----
1544 ----
1545 public: ----
1546 KernelOperandInfo(MachineOperand *MO, MachineRegisterInfo &MRI, 0
1547 const SmallPtrSetImpl &IllegalPhis) ----
1548 : MRI(MRI) { 0
1549 Source = MO; 0
1550 BB = MO->getParent()->getParent(); 0
1551 while (isRegInLoop(MO)) { 0
1552 MachineInstr *MI = MRI.getVRegDef(MO->getReg()); 0
1553 if (MI->isFullCopy()) { 0
1554 MO = &MI->getOperand(1); 0
1555 continue; 0
1556 } ----
1557 if (!MI->isPHI()) 0
1558 break; 0
1559 // If this is an illegal phi, don't count it in distance. ----
1560 if (IllegalPhis.count(MI)) { 0
1561 MO = &MI->getOperand(3); 0
1562 continue; 0
1563 } ----
1564 ----
1565 Register Default = getInitPhiReg(*MI, BB); 0
1566 MO = MI->getOperand(2).getMBB() == BB ? &MI->getOperand(1) 0
1567 : &MI->getOperand(3); 0
1568 PhiDefaults.push_back(Default); 0
1569 } ----
1570 Target = MO; 0
1571 } 0
1572 ----
1573 bool operator==(const KernelOperandInfo &Other) const { 0
1574 return PhiDefaults.size() == Other.PhiDefaults.size(); 0
1575 } ----
1576 ----
1577 void print(raw_ostream &OS) const { 0
1578 OS << "use of " << *Source << ": distance(" << PhiDefaults.size() << ") in " 0
1579 << *Source->getParent(); 0
1580 } 0
1581 ----
1582 private: ----
1583 bool isRegInLoop(MachineOperand *MO) { 0
1584 return MO->isReg() && MO->getReg().isVirtual() && 0
1585 MRI.getVRegDef(MO->getReg())->getParent() == BB; 0
1586 } ----
1587 }; ----
1588 } // namespace ----
1589 ----
1590 MachineBasicBlock * ----
1591 PeelingModuloScheduleExpander::peelKernel(LoopPeelDirection LPD) { 0
1592 MachineBasicBlock *NewBB = PeelSingleBlockLoop(LPD, BB, MRI, TII); 0
1593 if (LPD == LPD_Front) 0
1594 PeeledFront.push_back(NewBB); 0
1595 else ----
1596 PeeledBack.push_front(NewBB); 0
1597 for (auto I = BB->begin(), NI = NewBB->begin(); !I->isTerminator(); 0
1598 ++I, ++NI) { 0
1599 CanonicalMIs[&*I] = &*I; 0
1600 CanonicalMIs[&*NI] = &*I; 0
1601 BlockMIs[{NewBB, &*I}] = &*NI; 0
1602 BlockMIs[{BB, &*I}] = &*I; 0
1603 } ----
1604 return NewBB; 0
1605 } ----
1606 ----
1607 void PeelingModuloScheduleExpander::filterInstructions(MachineBasicBlock *MB, 0
1608 int MinStage) { ----
1609 for (auto I = MB->getFirstInstrTerminator()->getReverseIterator(); 0
1610 I != std::next(MB->getFirstNonPHI()->getReverseIterator());) { 0
1611 MachineInstr *MI = &*I++; 0
1612 int Stage = getStage(MI); 0
1613 if (Stage == -1 || Stage >= MinStage) 0
1614 continue; 0
1615 ----
1616 for (MachineOperand &DefMO : MI->defs()) { 0
1617 SmallVector, 4> Subs; 0
1618 for (MachineInstr &UseMI : MRI.use_instructions(DefMO.getReg())) { 0
1619 // Only PHIs can use values from this block by construction. ----
1620 // Match with the equivalent PHI in B. ----
1621 assert(UseMI.isPHI()); 0
1622 Register Reg = getEquivalentRegisterIn(UseMI.getOperand(0).getReg(), 0
1623 MI->getParent()); ----
1624 Subs.emplace_back(&UseMI, Reg); 0
1625 } ----
1626 for (auto &Sub : Subs) 0
1627 Sub.first->substituteRegister(DefMO.getReg(), Sub.second, /*SubIdx=*/0, 0
1628 *MRI.getTargetRegisterInfo()); 0
1629 } 0
1630 if (LIS) 0
1631 LIS->RemoveMachineInstrFromMaps(*MI); 0
1632 MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1633 } ----
1634 } 0
1635 ----
1636 void PeelingModuloScheduleExpander::moveStageBetweenBlocks( 0
1637 MachineBasicBlock *DestBB, MachineBasicBlock *SourceBB, unsigned Stage) { ----
1638 auto InsertPt = DestBB->getFirstNonPHI(); 0
1639 DenseMap Remaps; 0
1640 for (MachineInstr &MI : llvm::make_early_inc_range( 0
1641 llvm::make_range(SourceBB->getFirstNonPHI(), SourceBB->end()))) { 0
1642 if (MI.isPHI()) { 0
1643 // This is an illegal PHI. If we move any instructions using an illegal ----
1644 // PHI, we need to create a legal Phi. ----
1645 if (getStage(&MI) != Stage) { 0
1646 // The legal Phi is not necessary if the illegal phi's stage ----
1647 // is being moved. ----
1648 Register PhiR = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1649 auto RC = MRI.getRegClass(PhiR); 0
1650 Register NR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1651 MachineInstr *NI = BuildMI(*DestBB, DestBB->getFirstNonPHI(), 0
1652 DebugLoc(), TII->get(TargetOpcode::PHI), NR) 0
1653 .addReg(PhiR) 0
1654 .addMBB(SourceBB); 0
1655 BlockMIs[{DestBB, CanonicalMIs[&MI]}] = NI; 0
1656 CanonicalMIs[NI] = CanonicalMIs[&MI]; 0
1657 Remaps[PhiR] = NR; 0
1658 } ----
1659 } ----
1660 if (getStage(&MI) != Stage) 0
1661 continue; 0
1662 MI.removeFromParent(); 0
1663 DestBB->insert(InsertPt, &MI); 0
1664 auto *KernelMI = CanonicalMIs[&MI]; 0
1665 BlockMIs[{DestBB, KernelMI}] = &MI; 0
1666 BlockMIs.erase({SourceBB, KernelMI}); 0
1667 } ----
1668 SmallVector PhiToDelete; 0
1669 for (MachineInstr &MI : DestBB->phis()) { 0
1670 assert(MI.getNumOperands() == 3); 0
1671 MachineInstr *Def = MRI.getVRegDef(MI.getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1672 // If the instruction referenced by the phi is moved inside the block ----
1673 // we don't need the phi anymore. ----
1674 if (getStage(Def) == Stage) { 0
1675 Register PhiReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1676 assert(Def->findRegisterDefOperandIdx(MI.getOperand(1).getReg()) != -1); 0
1677 MRI.replaceRegWith(MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), MI.getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1678 MI.getOperand(0).setReg(PhiReg); 0
1679 PhiToDelete.push_back(&MI); 0
1680 } ----
1681 } ----
1682 for (auto *P : PhiToDelete) 0
1683 P->eraseFromParent(); 0
1684 InsertPt = DestBB->getFirstNonPHI(); 0
1685 // Helper to clone Phi instructions into the destination block. We clone Phi ----
1686 // greedily to avoid combinatorial explosion of Phi instructions. ----
1687 auto clonePhi = [&](MachineInstr *Phi) { 0
1688 MachineInstr *NewMI = MF.CloneMachineInstr(Phi); 0
1689 DestBB->insert(InsertPt, NewMI); 0
1690 Register OrigR = Phi->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1691 Register R = MRI.createVirtualRegister(MRI.getRegClass(OrigR)); 0
1692 NewMI->getOperand(0).setReg(R); 0
1693 NewMI->getOperand(1).setReg(OrigR); 0
1694 NewMI->getOperand(2).setMBB(*DestBB->pred_begin()); 0
1695 Remaps[OrigR] = R; 0
1696 CanonicalMIs[NewMI] = CanonicalMIs[Phi]; 0
1697 BlockMIs[{DestBB, CanonicalMIs[Phi]}] = NewMI; 0
1698 PhiNodeLoopIteration[NewMI] = PhiNodeLoopIteration[Phi]; 0
1699 return R; 0
1700 }; 0
1701 for (auto I = DestBB->getFirstNonPHI(); I != DestBB->end(); ++I) { 0
1702 for (MachineOperand &MO : I->uses()) { 0
1703 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
1704 continue; 0
1705 if (Remaps.count(MO.getReg())) 0
1706 MO.setReg(Remaps[MO.getReg()]); 0
1707 else { ----
1708 // If we are using a phi from the source block we need to add a new phi ----
1709 // pointing to the old one. ----
1710 MachineInstr *Use = MRI.getUniqueVRegDef(MO.getReg()); 0
1711 if (Use && Use->isPHI() && Use->getParent() == SourceBB) { 0
1712 Register R = clonePhi(Use); 0
1713 MO.setReg(R); 0
1714 } ----
1715 } ----
1716 } ----
1717 } ----
1718 } 0
1719 ----
1720 Register ----
1721 PeelingModuloScheduleExpander::getPhiCanonicalReg(MachineInstr *CanonicalPhi, 0
1722 MachineInstr *Phi) { ----
1723 unsigned distance = PhiNodeLoopIteration[Phi]; 0
1724 MachineInstr *CanonicalUse = CanonicalPhi; 0
1725 Register CanonicalUseReg = CanonicalUse->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1726 for (unsigned I = 0; I < distance; ++I) { 0
1727 assert(CanonicalUse->isPHI()); 0
1728 assert(CanonicalUse->getNumOperands() == 5); 0
1729 unsigned LoopRegIdx = 3, InitRegIdx = 1; 0
1730 if (CanonicalUse->getOperand(2).getMBB() == CanonicalUse->getParent()) 0
1731 std::swap(LoopRegIdx, InitRegIdx); 0
1732 CanonicalUseReg = CanonicalUse->getOperand(LoopRegIdx).getReg(); 0
1733 CanonicalUse = MRI.getVRegDef(CanonicalUseReg); 0
1734 } ----
1735 return CanonicalUseReg; 0
1736 } ----
1737 ----
1738 void PeelingModuloScheduleExpander::peelPrologAndEpilogs() { 0
1739 BitVector LS(Schedule.getNumStages(), true); 0
1740 BitVector AS(Schedule.getNumStages(), true); 0
1741 LiveStages[BB] = LS; 0
1742 AvailableStages[BB] = AS; 0
1743 ----
1744 // Peel out the prologs. ----
1745 LS.reset(); 0
1746 for (int I = 0; I < Schedule.getNumStages() - 1; ++I) { 0
1747 LS[I] = true; 0
1748 Prologs.push_back(peelKernel(LPD_Front)); 0
1749 LiveStages[Prologs.back()] = LS; 0
1750 AvailableStages[Prologs.back()] = LS; 0
1751 } ----
1752 ----
1753 // Create a block that will end up as the new loop exiting block (dominated by ----
1754 // all prologs and epilogs). It will only contain PHIs, in the same order as ----
1755 // BB's PHIs. This gives us a poor-man's LCSSA with the inductive property ----
1756 // that the exiting block is a (sub) clone of BB. This in turn gives us the ----
1757 // property that any value deffed in BB but used outside of BB is used by a ----
1758 // PHI in the exiting block. ----
1759 MachineBasicBlock *ExitingBB = CreateLCSSAExitingBlock(); 0
1760 EliminateDeadPhis(ExitingBB, MRI, LIS, /*KeepSingleSrcPhi=*/true); 0
1761 // Push out the epilogs, again in reverse order. ----
1762 // We can't assume anything about the minumum loop trip count at this point, ----
1763 // so emit a fairly complex epilog. ----
1764 ----
1765 // We first peel number of stages minus one epilogue. Then we remove dead ----
1766 // stages and reorder instructions based on their stage. If we have 3 stages ----
1767 // we generate first: ----
1768 // E0[3, 2, 1] ----
1769 // E1[3', 2'] ----
1770 // E2[3''] ----
1771 // And then we move instructions based on their stages to have: ----
1772 // E0[3] ----
1773 // E1[2, 3'] ----
1774 // E2[1, 2', 3''] ----
1775 // The transformation is legal because we only move instructions past ----
1776 // instructions of a previous loop iteration. ----
1777 for (int I = 1; I <= Schedule.getNumStages() - 1; ++I) { 0
1778 Epilogs.push_back(peelKernel(LPD_Back)); 0
1779 MachineBasicBlock *B = Epilogs.back(); 0
1780 filterInstructions(B, Schedule.getNumStages() - I); 0
1781 // Keep track at which iteration each phi belongs to. We need it to know ----
1782 // what version of the variable to use during prologue/epilogue stitching. ----
1783 EliminateDeadPhis(B, MRI, LIS, /*KeepSingleSrcPhi=*/true); 0
1784 for (MachineInstr &Phi : B->phis()) 0
1785 PhiNodeLoopIteration[&Phi] = Schedule.getNumStages() - I; 0
1786 } ----
1787 for (size_t I = 0; I < Epilogs.size(); I++) { 0
1788 LS.reset(); 0
1789 for (size_t J = I; J < Epilogs.size(); J++) { 0
1790 int Iteration = J; 0
1791 unsigned Stage = Schedule.getNumStages() - 1 + I - J; 0
1792 // Move stage one block at a time so that Phi nodes are updated correctly. ----
1793 for (size_t K = Iteration; K > I; K--) 0
1794 moveStageBetweenBlocks(Epilogs[K - 1], Epilogs[K], Stage); 0
1795 LS[Stage] = true; 0
1796 } ----
1797 LiveStages[Epilogs[I]] = LS; 0
1798 AvailableStages[Epilogs[I]] = AS; 0
1799 } ----
1800 ----
1801 // Now we've defined all the prolog and epilog blocks as a fallthrough ----
1802 // sequence, add the edges that will be followed if the loop trip count is ----
1803 // lower than the number of stages (connecting prologs directly with epilogs). ----
1804 auto PI = Prologs.begin(); 0
1805 auto EI = Epilogs.begin(); 0
1806 assert(Prologs.size() == Epilogs.size()); 0
1807 for (; PI != Prologs.end(); ++PI, ++EI) { 0
1808 MachineBasicBlock *Pred = *(*EI)->pred_begin(); 0
1809 (*PI)->addSuccessor(*EI); 0
1810 for (MachineInstr &MI : (*EI)->phis()) { 0
1811 Register Reg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1812 MachineInstr *Use = MRI.getUniqueVRegDef(Reg); 0
1813 if (Use && Use->getParent() == Pred) { 0
1814 MachineInstr *CanonicalUse = CanonicalMIs[Use]; 0
1815 if (CanonicalUse->isPHI()) { 0
1816 // If the use comes from a phi we need to skip as many phi as the ----
1817 // distance between the epilogue and the kernel. Trace through the phi ----
1818 // chain to find the right value. ----
1819 Reg = getPhiCanonicalReg(CanonicalUse, Use); 0
1820 } ----
1821 Reg = getEquivalentRegisterIn(Reg, *PI); 0
1822 } ----
1823 MI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateReg(Reg, /*isDef=*/false)); 0
1824 MI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateMBB(*PI)); 0
1825 } ----
1826 } ----
1827 ----
1828 // Create a list of all blocks in order. ----
1829 SmallVector Blocks; 0
1830 llvm::copy(PeeledFront, std::back_inserter(Blocks)); 0
1831 Blocks.push_back(BB); 0
1832 llvm::copy(PeeledBack, std::back_inserter(Blocks)); 0
1833 ----
1834 // Iterate in reverse order over all instructions, remapping as we go. ----
1835 for (MachineBasicBlock *B : reverse(Blocks)) { 0
1836 for (auto I = B->instr_rbegin(); 0
1837 I != std::next(B->getFirstNonPHI()->getReverseIterator());) { 0
1838 MachineBasicBlock::reverse_instr_iterator MI = I++; 0
1839 rewriteUsesOf(&*MI); 0
1840 } ----
1841 } ----
1842 for (auto *MI : IllegalPhisToDelete) { 0
1843 if (LIS) 0
1844 LIS->RemoveMachineInstrFromMaps(*MI); 0
1845 MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1846 } ----
1847 IllegalPhisToDelete.clear(); 0
1848 ----
1849 // Now all remapping has been done, we're free to optimize the generated code. ----
1850 for (MachineBasicBlock *B : reverse(Blocks)) 0
1851 EliminateDeadPhis(B, MRI, LIS); 0
1852 EliminateDeadPhis(ExitingBB, MRI, LIS); 0
1853 } 0
1854 ----
1855 MachineBasicBlock *PeelingModuloScheduleExpander::CreateLCSSAExitingBlock() { 0
1856 MachineFunction &MF = *BB->getParent(); 0
1857 MachineBasicBlock *Exit = *BB->succ_begin(); 0
1858 if (Exit == BB) 0
1859 Exit = *std::next(BB->succ_begin()); 0
1860 ----
1861 MachineBasicBlock *NewBB = MF.CreateMachineBasicBlock(BB->getBasicBlock()); 0
1862 MF.insert(std::next(BB->getIterator()), NewBB); 0
1863 ----
1864 // Clone all phis in BB into NewBB and rewrite. ----
1865 for (MachineInstr &MI : BB->phis()) { 0
1866 auto RC = MRI.getRegClass(MI.getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1867 Register OldR = MI.getOperand(3).getReg(); 0
1868 Register R = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1869 SmallVector Uses; 0
1870 for (MachineInstr &Use : MRI.use_instructions(OldR)) 0
1871 if (Use.getParent() != BB) 0
1872 Uses.push_back(&Use); 0
1873 for (MachineInstr *Use : Uses) 0
1874 Use->substituteRegister(OldR, R, /*SubIdx=*/0, 0
1875 *MRI.getTargetRegisterInfo()); 0
1876 MachineInstr *NI = BuildMI(NewBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(TargetOpcode::PHI), R) 0
1877 .addReg(OldR) 0
1878 .addMBB(BB); 0
1879 BlockMIs[{NewBB, &MI}] = NI; 0
1880 CanonicalMIs[NI] = &MI; 0
1881 } 0
1882 BB->replaceSuccessor(Exit, NewBB); 0
1883 Exit->replacePhiUsesWith(BB, NewBB); 0
1884 NewBB->addSuccessor(Exit); 0
1885 ----
1886 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = nullptr, *FBB = nullptr; 0
1887 SmallVector Cond; 0
1888 bool CanAnalyzeBr = !TII->analyzeBranch(*BB, TBB, FBB, Cond); 0
1889 (void)CanAnalyzeBr; ----
1890 assert(CanAnalyzeBr && "Must be able to analyze the loop branch!"); 0
1891 TII->removeBranch(*BB); 0
1892 TII->insertBranch(*BB, TBB == Exit ? NewBB : TBB, FBB == Exit ? NewBB : FBB, 0
1893 Cond, DebugLoc()); 0
1894 TII->insertUnconditionalBranch(*NewBB, Exit, DebugLoc()); 0
1895 return NewBB; 0
1896 } 0
1897 ----
1898 Register ----
1899 PeelingModuloScheduleExpander::getEquivalentRegisterIn(Register Reg, 0
1900 MachineBasicBlock *BB) { ----
1901 MachineInstr *MI = MRI.getUniqueVRegDef(Reg); 0
1902 unsigned OpIdx = MI->findRegisterDefOperandIdx(Reg); 0
1903 return BlockMIs[{BB, CanonicalMIs[MI]}]->getOperand(OpIdx).getReg(); 0
1904 } ----
1905 ----
1906 void PeelingModuloScheduleExpander::rewriteUsesOf(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1907 if (MI->isPHI()) { 0
1908 // This is an illegal PHI. The loop-carried (desired) value is operand 3, ----
1909 // and it is produced by this block. ----
1910 Register PhiR = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1911 Register R = MI->getOperand(3).getReg(); 0
1912 int RMIStage = getStage(MRI.getUniqueVRegDef(R)); 0
1913 if (RMIStage != -1 && !AvailableStages[MI->getParent()].test(RMIStage)) 0
1914 R = MI->getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1915 MRI.setRegClass(R, MRI.getRegClass(PhiR)); 0
1916 MRI.replaceRegWith(PhiR, R); 0
1917 // Postpone deleting the Phi as it may be referenced by BlockMIs and used ----
1918 // later to figure out how to remap registers. ----
1919 MI->getOperand(0).setReg(PhiR); 0
1920 IllegalPhisToDelete.push_back(MI); 0
1921 return; 0
1922 } ----
1923 ----
1924 int Stage = getStage(MI); 0
1925 if (Stage == -1 || LiveStages.count(MI->getParent()) == 0 || 0
1926 LiveStages[MI->getParent()].test(Stage)) 0
1927 // Instruction is live, no rewriting to do. ----
1928 return; 0
1929 ----
1930 for (MachineOperand &DefMO : MI->defs()) { 0
1931 SmallVector, 4> Subs; 0
1932 for (MachineInstr &UseMI : MRI.use_instructions(DefMO.getReg())) { 0
1933 // Only PHIs can use values from this block by construction. ----
1934 // Match with the equivalent PHI in B. ----
1935 assert(UseMI.isPHI()); 0
1936 Register Reg = getEquivalentRegisterIn(UseMI.getOperand(0).getReg(), 0
1937 MI->getParent()); ----
1938 Subs.emplace_back(&UseMI, Reg); 0
1939 } ----
1940 for (auto &Sub : Subs) 0
1941 Sub.first->substituteRegister(DefMO.getReg(), Sub.second, /*SubIdx=*/0, 0
1942 *MRI.getTargetRegisterInfo()); 0
1943 } 0
1944 if (LIS) 0
1945 LIS->RemoveMachineInstrFromMaps(*MI); 0
1946 MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1947 } ----
1948 ----
1949 void PeelingModuloScheduleExpander::fixupBranches() { 0
1950 // Work outwards from the kernel. ----
1951 bool KernelDisposed = false; 0
1952 int TC = Schedule.getNumStages() - 1; 0
1953 for (auto PI = Prologs.rbegin(), EI = Epilogs.rbegin(); PI != Prologs.rend(); 0
1954 ++PI, ++EI, --TC) { 0
1955 MachineBasicBlock *Prolog = *PI; 0
1956 MachineBasicBlock *Fallthrough = *Prolog->succ_begin(); 0
1957 MachineBasicBlock *Epilog = *EI; 0
1958 SmallVector Cond; 0
1959 TII->removeBranch(*Prolog); 0
1960 std::optional StaticallyGreater = ----
1961 LoopInfo->createTripCountGreaterCondition(TC, *Prolog, Cond); 0
1962 if (!StaticallyGreater) { 0
1963 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Dynamic: TC > " << TC << "\n"); 0
1964 // Dynamically branch based on Cond. ----
1965 TII->insertBranch(*Prolog, Epilog, Fallthrough, Cond, DebugLoc()); 0
1966 } else if (*StaticallyGreater == false) { 0
1967 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Static-false: TC > " << TC << "\n"); 0
1968 // Prolog never falls through; branch to epilog and orphan interior ----
1969 // blocks. Leave it to unreachable-block-elim to clean up. ----
1970 Prolog->removeSuccessor(Fallthrough); 0
1971 for (MachineInstr &P : Fallthrough->phis()) { 0
1972 P.removeOperand(2); 0
1973 P.removeOperand(1); 0
1974 } ----
1975 TII->insertUnconditionalBranch(*Prolog, Epilog, DebugLoc()); 0
1976 KernelDisposed = true; 0
1977 } else { ----
1978 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Static-true: TC > " << TC << "\n"); 0
1979 // Prolog always falls through; remove incoming values in epilog. ----
1980 Prolog->removeSuccessor(Epilog); 0
1981 for (MachineInstr &P : Epilog->phis()) { 0
1982 P.removeOperand(4); 0
1983 P.removeOperand(3); 0
1984 } ----
1985 } ----
1986 } 0
1987 ----
1988 if (!KernelDisposed) { 0
1989 LoopInfo->adjustTripCount(-(Schedule.getNumStages() - 1)); 0
1990 LoopInfo->setPreheader(Prologs.back()); 0
1991 } else { ----
1992 LoopInfo->disposed(); 0
1993 } ----
1994 } 0
1995 ----
1996 void PeelingModuloScheduleExpander::rewriteKernel() { 0
1997 KernelRewriter KR(*Schedule.getLoop(), Schedule, BB); 0
1998 KR.rewrite(); 0
1999 } 0
2000 ----
2001 void PeelingModuloScheduleExpander::expand() { 0
2002 BB = Schedule.getLoop()->getTopBlock(); 0
2003 Preheader = Schedule.getLoop()->getLoopPreheader(); 0
2004 LLVM_DEBUG(Schedule.dump()); 0
2005 LoopInfo = TII->analyzeLoopForPipelining(BB); 0
2006 assert(LoopInfo); 0
2007 ----
2008 rewriteKernel(); 0
2009 peelPrologAndEpilogs(); 0
2010 fixupBranches(); 0
2011 } 0
2012 ----
2013 void PeelingModuloScheduleExpander::validateAgainstModuloScheduleExpander() { 0
2014 BB = Schedule.getLoop()->getTopBlock(); 0
2015 Preheader = Schedule.getLoop()->getLoopPreheader(); 0
2016 ----
2017 // Dump the schedule before we invalidate and remap all its instructions. ----
2018 // Stash it in a string so we can print it if we found an error. ----
2019 std::string ScheduleDump; 0
2020 raw_string_ostream OS(ScheduleDump); 0
2021 Schedule.print(OS); 0
2022 OS.flush(); 0
2023 ----
2024 // First, run the normal ModuleScheduleExpander. We don't support any ----
2025 // InstrChanges. ----
2026 assert(LIS && "Requires LiveIntervals!"); 0
2027 ModuloScheduleExpander MSE(MF, Schedule, *LIS, 0
2028 ModuloScheduleExpander::InstrChangesTy()); 0
2029 MSE.expand(); 0
2030 MachineBasicBlock *ExpandedKernel = MSE.getRewrittenKernel(); 0
2031 if (!ExpandedKernel) { 0
2032 // The expander optimized away the kernel. We can't do any useful checking. ----
2033 MSE.cleanup(); 0
2034 return; 0
2035 } ----
2036 // Before running the KernelRewriter, re-add BB into the CFG. ----
2037 Preheader->addSuccessor(BB); 0
2038 ----
2039 // Now run the new expansion algorithm. ----
2040 KernelRewriter KR(*Schedule.getLoop(), Schedule, BB); 0
2041 KR.rewrite(); 0
2042 peelPrologAndEpilogs(); 0
2043 ----
2044 // Collect all illegal phis that the new algorithm created. We'll give these ----
2045 // to KernelOperandInfo. ----
2046 SmallPtrSet IllegalPhis; 0
2047 for (auto NI = BB->getFirstNonPHI(); NI != BB->end(); ++NI) { 0
2048 if (NI->isPHI()) 0
2049 IllegalPhis.insert(&*NI); 0
2050 } ----
2051 ----
2052 // Co-iterate across both kernels. We expect them to be identical apart from ----
2053 // phis and full COPYs (we look through both). ----
2054 SmallVector, 8> KOIs; 0
2055 auto OI = ExpandedKernel->begin(); 0
2056 auto NI = BB->begin(); 0
2057 for (; !OI->isTerminator() && !NI->isTerminator(); ++OI, ++NI) { 0
2058 while (OI->isPHI() || OI->isFullCopy()) 0
2059 ++OI; 0
2060 while (NI->isPHI() || NI->isFullCopy()) 0
2061 ++NI; 0
2062 assert(OI->getOpcode() == NI->getOpcode() && "Opcodes don't match?!"); 0
2063 // Analyze every operand separately. ----
2064 for (auto OOpI = OI->operands_begin(), NOpI = NI->operands_begin(); 0
2065 OOpI != OI->operands_end(); ++OOpI, ++NOpI) 0
2066 KOIs.emplace_back(KernelOperandInfo(&*OOpI, MRI, IllegalPhis), 0
2067 KernelOperandInfo(&*NOpI, MRI, IllegalPhis)); 0
2068 } ----
2069 ----
2070 bool Failed = false; 0
2071 for (auto &OldAndNew : KOIs) { 0
2072 if (OldAndNew.first == OldAndNew.second) 0
2073 continue; 0
2074 Failed = true; 0
2075 errs() << "Modulo kernel validation error: [\n"; 0
2076 errs() << " [golden] "; 0
2077 OldAndNew.first.print(errs()); 0
2078 errs() << " "; 0
2079 OldAndNew.second.print(errs()); 0
2080 errs() << "]\n"; 0
2081 } ----
2082 ----
2083 if (Failed) { 0
2084 errs() << "Golden reference kernel:\n"; 0
2085 ExpandedKernel->print(errs()); 0
2086 errs() << "New kernel:\n"; 0
2087 BB->print(errs()); 0
2088 errs() << ScheduleDump; 0
2089 report_fatal_error( 0
2090 "Modulo kernel validation (-pipeliner-experimental-cg) failed"); ----
2091 } ----
2092 ----
2093 // Cleanup by removing BB from the CFG again as the original ----
2094 // ModuloScheduleExpander intended. ----
2095 Preheader->removeSuccessor(BB); 0
2096 MSE.cleanup(); 0
2097 } 0
2098 ----

2102 // This pass constructs a ModuloSchedule from its module and runs ----
2103 // ModuloScheduleExpander. ----
2104 // ----
2105 // The module is expected to contain a single-block analyzable loop. ----
2106 // The total order of instructions is taken from the loop as-is. ----
2107 // Instructions are expected to be annotated with a PostInstrSymbol. ----
2108 // This PostInstrSymbol must have the following format: ----
2109 // "Stage=%d Cycle=%d". ----
2110 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2111 ----

2113 class ModuloScheduleTest : public MachineFunctionPass { ----
2114 public: ----
2115 static char ID; ----
2116 ----
2117 ModuloScheduleTest() : MachineFunctionPass(ID) { 0
2118 initializeModuloScheduleTestPass(*PassRegistry::getPassRegistry()); 0
2119 } 0

2122 void runOnLoop(MachineFunction &MF, MachineLoop &L); ----
2123 ----

2125 AU.addRequired(); 0
2126 AU.addRequired(); 0
2127 MachineFunctionPass::getAnalysisUsage(AU); 0
2128 } 0
2129 }; ----

2135 "Modulo Schedule test pass", false, false) ----
2136 INITIALIZE_PASS_DEPENDENCY(MachineLoopInfo) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2137 INITIALIZE_PASS_DEPENDENCY(LiveIntervals) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

2141 bool ModuloScheduleTest::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
2142 MachineLoopInfo &MLI = getAnalysis(); 0
2143 for (auto *L : MLI) { 0
2144 if (L->getTopBlock() != L->getBottomBlock()) 0
2145 continue; 0
2146 runOnLoop(MF, *L); 0
2147 return false; 0
2148 } ----
2149 return false; 0
2150 } ----
2151 ----
2152 static void parseSymbolString(StringRef S, int &Cycle, int &Stage) { 0
2153 std::pair StageAndCycle = getToken(S, "_"); 0
2154 std::pair StageTokenAndValue = ----
2155 getToken(StageAndCycle.first, "-"); 0
2156 std::pair CycleTokenAndValue = ----
2157 getToken(StageAndCycle.second, "-"); 0
2158 if (StageTokenAndValue.first != "Stage" || 0
2159 CycleTokenAndValue.first != "_Cycle") { 0
2160 llvm_unreachable( 0
2161 "Bad post-instr symbol syntax: see comment in ModuloScheduleTest"); ----
2162 return; ----
2163 } ----
2164 ----
2165 StageTokenAndValue.second.drop_front().getAsInteger(10, Stage); 0
2166 CycleTokenAndValue.second.drop_front().getAsInteger(10, Cycle); 0
2167 ----
2168 dbgs() << " Stage=" << Stage << ", Cycle=" << Cycle << "\n"; 0
2169 } ----
2170 ----
2171 void ModuloScheduleTest::runOnLoop(MachineFunction &MF, MachineLoop &L) { 0
2172 LiveIntervals &LIS = getAnalysis(); 0
2173 MachineBasicBlock *BB = L.getTopBlock(); 0
2174 dbgs() << "--- ModuloScheduleTest running on BB#" << BB->getNumber() << "\n"; 0
2175 ----
2176 DenseMap Cycle, Stage; 0
2177 std::vector Instrs; 0
2178 for (MachineInstr &MI : *BB) { 0
2179 if (MI.isTerminator()) 0
2180 continue; 0
2181 Instrs.push_back(&MI); 0
2182 if (MCSymbol *Sym = MI.getPostInstrSymbol()) { 0
2183 dbgs() << "Parsing post-instr symbol for " << MI; 0
2184 parseSymbolString(Sym->getName(), Cycle[&MI], Stage[&MI]); 0
2185 } ----
2186 } ----
2187 ----
2188 ModuloSchedule MS(MF, &L, std::move(Instrs), std::move(Cycle), 0
2189 std::move(Stage)); 0
2190 ModuloScheduleExpander MSE( ----
2191 MF, MS, LIS, /*InstrChanges=*/ModuloScheduleExpander::InstrChangesTy()); 0
2192 MSE.expand(); 0
2193 MSE.cleanup(); 0
2194 } 0

2196 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2197 // ModuloScheduleTestAnnotater implementation ----
2198 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2199 ----
2200 void ModuloScheduleTestAnnotater::annotate() { 0
2201 for (MachineInstr *MI : S.getInstructions()) { 0
2202 SmallVector SV; 0
